title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with the 1 cup of water and stir until sugar and cocoa dissolve.
Heat to boiling and remove from heat. Add the 2 milks and water; return to heat but do not boil.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together eggs, butter, salt, pepper, onion, celery flakes and milk and chicken juice.
Pour over chicken and bread.
On top of this, put slices of Velveeta cheese, and soup.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
May be covered and refrigerated overnight. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; cut into small pieces.
Cook elbow macaroni and drain.
Mix chicken, soups, macaroni and sour cream. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in 1 large or 2 small casserole dishes.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbled up crackers, then pour crumbs over casserole.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook butter, onion and flour until thick.
Mix flour mixture with salt, pepper, sugar, sour cream and grated cheese.
Mix lightly with beans.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat rolls
directions: Make a fine crust with the flour, shortening and salt; mix and roll thin.
Cut in 3-inch squares.
Spread with seasoned ham. Moisten with a little stock or milk.
Roll up like a jelly roll, pressing the ends tightly together.
Bake in a 450° oven and serve hot.

title: cream cheese brownie delights
directions: Mix together and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Cut into squares.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in pan; cook over low heat until chocolate melts.
Combine marshmallows and peanuts in large bowl; add the chocolate mixture.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper and spread mixture evenly.
Chill for 2 hours in freezer. Cut in squares or cut in pieces.

title: taco salad
directions: Finely chop first five ingredients.
Cook hamburg per directions on back of taco mix.
Crush bag of Doritos very fine. Mix all ingredients with Catalina salad dressing.
Chill.
(Mix ingredients about five hours before serving.) Do not mix overnight.
Enjoy!

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Set aside 1/2 cup.
Store remaining mix in an airtight container for later use.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and put in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix rice, Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and margarine on stove top until all is melted and mixed thoroughly.
Place broccoli cuts in bottom of casserole dish and pour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Let potatoes get to room temperature.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle melted butter over potatoes.
Mix milk and cream of celery soup.
Spread over potatoes.
Top with crushed onion rings.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.
(Can be made a day ahead and baked when ready to use.)

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and chop.
Add ingredients to taste.
Amount of seasoning depends on amount of meat.
Add mayonnaise to your desired consistency.
Mix well.
Refrigerate. Add seedless grapes, if desired.

title: north dallas chili
directions: Sear meat until gray.
Add water and onion.
Cook for 1 hour and add remaining ingredients. Cook, covered, in a Dutch oven for 45 minutes.
Remove lid and cook until desired consistency. Freezes very well.
(This was a State Fair of Texas prize winning recipe.)

title: raspberry christmas slush
directions: Heat water and sugar until dissolved.
Add juices and freeze. Take from freezer an hour before serving to soften.
Mix with ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Using a teaspoon of batter, form a ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet and mash with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: snowball surprises
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour and pecans. Chill. Shape 1 tablespoon dough around a chocolate kiss.
Cover kiss completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until set but not brown, about 12 minutes.
While warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Chill for a few hours.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain.
In large pot, combine spaghetti sauce, pepperoni, garlic salt and Italian seasoning. Add meat mixture.
Cook for 20 minutes.
(If mushrooms are canned, add to rest of ingredients.
If fresh, add last.)
Cook shells separately until done; drain.
Layer shells, meat and sauce mixture and Mozzarella cheese in large casserole dish.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese style asparagus
directions: Heat large skillet; add salad oil and when hot, add the asparagus.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Cover.
Lift skillet slightly above high heat and shake it constantly while cooking. Cook asparagus only until tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium if necessary, during last minute or so of cooking.
Don't overcook!

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, cook wings in oil on high heat, stirring constantly, until wings are browned.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook about 25 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Reheat before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Melt together caramels, butter and milk in a double boiler.
Pour half of cake mix into greased
and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: sausage pop ins
directions: Cook sausage; drain and crumble.
Mix in cream cheese until spreadable.
Cut each slice of bread in 1/2 (24 rectangles). Spread sausage cheese mix on each rectangle.
Roll bread up and wrap one piece of bacon around it.
Secure with wooden toothpick. Bake 15 minutes at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Make 24 snacks.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together with hands. Roll into bite size balls. Freeze on cookie sheet. Store in plastic bag until needed. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: new potato salad
directions: Steam potatoes until done.
When cool, cut into 1/2 or 1/4. Chop the bacon and microwave.
Add onion, bacon, horseradish and dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Heat soup on low heat.
Stir in gelatine and cream cheese until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a mold of your choice and chill overnight.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Beat them.
Add sifted flour which has been sifted a second time with salt and baking powder.
Add walnuts and vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, eggs, salt, pepper, onions and 1/2 can of tomato soup together.

title: egg drop soup
directions: For this recipe, you reduce the broth to intensify the flavor, infusing it with garlic and spices.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients but chicken in large shallow bowl. Cut wing in two pieces at joint and add to marinade.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from marinade and broil five inches from the heat, turning frequently, until well browned and cooked through. Serve hot or cold.

title: date-pineapple-pecan bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine all ingredients.
Blend well. Spread in well-greased loaf pan (9 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box in sheet cake pan.
Combine sugar, milk and marshmallows.
Heat until marshmallows are melted. Add coconut.
Pour over warm cake.

title: traveling coleslaw
directions: Heat first 7 ingredients.
Mix cabbage, onion, pepper and pimentos.
Pour liquid over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Mix with soups, tomatoes and taco sauce.
In large casserole, put layer of Doritos, layer of meat mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Repeat a second layer.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and chill.
Cut into bars.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts).
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: german slaw
directions: Mix
cabbage, onion and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
In a saucepan
combine
1 tablespoon sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar. Boil
until
sugar and salt dissolve; then add salad oil and bring
to a boil.
Add celery seed.
Pour boiling mixture over cabbage
and
mix well.
Put in covered container (large jars
do well).
Refrigerate
for
12 to 14 hours.
Turn jars over
once or twice.
Will keep several days in refrigerator. Makes approximately 1/2 gallon.

title: veggie salad
directions: Brown, drain and dice bacon.
In a separate bowl, mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cut up veggies, cheese and bacon.
Mix well and chill about 1 hour.

title: cucumber pickle
directions: Wash cucumbers with brush and dry thoroughly and pack in jars. Boil all other ingredients together.
Cool and pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: upside-down chocolate cake
directions: Mix the butter with 3/4 cup sugar.
Add the milk, 2 tablespoons cocoa and flour.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour; continue beating well.
Add lemon flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Brown the onion in the margarine in a large skillet or Dutch oven pan.
Meanwhile, cook the broccoli on High in the microwave. Add broccoli and the other ingredients and cook
until bubbly. Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce.
Stir thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour. Serve over lettuce chunks.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Take off bone.
Combine cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup, 1 can of broth from chicken and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil and add chicken.
Cook to desired consistency.

title: oatmeal bread(very light, excellent toasted and great with cheese)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir in sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour boiling water over oatmeal and add molasses, salt and shortening. Let stand until lukewarm, then add yeast mixture and beat well.
Add enough flour to make a stiff mixture without being too sticky.
Form into a large soft ball.
Cover and let rise until twice the original size. Make sure it is placed in a dry warm place.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream oleo; gradually add sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Blend together the dry ingredients; add egg yolks alternately with milk.
Blend just to mix.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, nuts and lemon peel.
Turn into 3 medium size loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate in the milk over low heat.
Beat sugar into the cream cheese.
Add the milk and chocolate mixture to the cream cheese mixture; beat until smooth.
Add in Cool Whip.
Spoon in crust; freeze for 4 hours.

title: ham cheesecake appetizer
directions: Grease spring-form pan 9 x 3-inches.
Coat sides and bottom with bread crumbs.
Spread any remaining crumbs evenly on bottom of pan.
Beat half and half, mustard, salt, red pepper, eggs and cream cheese in large bowl on medium speed until smooth, about 5 minutes. Stir in ham and Swiss cheese.
Spread in pan.
Bake in 325° oven until set, about 1 hour.
Cool and refrigerate no longer than 48 hours.

title: christmas punch
directions: Bring to a boil. Ready to serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until clear and thick. Remove from heat and add strawberry jello minus 1 tablespoon. Stir thoroughly	and let cool.
Slice strawberries and put in cooked pie
shell.
After	the mixture is cool, pour over the strawberries.
Top	with
Cool
Whip.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: brazilian chicken in beer
directions: Marinate the chicken overnight in vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Spread chicken with mayonnaise, then wrap a piece of bacon around each piece of chicken.
Arrange in a pan, then pour the beer over it.
Bake at 400°.
Turn the chicken (so the bacon will be crisp).
Serves 8 people.
Serve with rice, vegetables or salad.

title: grandma o'neill's irish soda bread
directions: Combine buttermilk and eggs.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients (flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, baking soda and caraway seed) in a large bowl.
Using your fingers, work softened butter into the dry mixture until butter is the size of small peas and evenly distributed.
Stir in raisins.
Pour buttermilk and eggs into the dry mixture until mixture is moist.
If mixture is too moist, add a little extra flour.
Pour onto a floured surface. Shape into a large rounded loaf (or put into two 9 x 5-inch oiled loaf pans) and put on a teflon tray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Enjoy!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl beat sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Press candy kiss in center of each ball immediately after baking.

title: recipe for life
directions: Mix all together.
This is to be mixed well with tears of joy and sorrow and sympathy.
It is flavored with little gifts of love and kindly service.
Four cups of prayer and faith are used to lighten the other ingredients and to raise the texture to great height in daily living.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and put in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: simple spaghetti sauce
directions: Empty tomato sauce into a 2-quart saucepan.
Into this, stir in the Italian seasoning, parsley, garlic salt, sugar, pepper and chopped onion.
Cover and simmer while browning hamburger in frying pan.
After browned, add to sauce.
Simmer for 4 hours, or until it has a well-seasoned taste.
Serve over pasta of your choice.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: r.s. peanut brittle
directions: Cook until it forms a soft ball, then add peanuts and butter. Cook until brown in color.
Add soda.
Stir well and pour up quickly.

title: cream custard for fruit
directions: Combine brown sugar and milk in heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat until mixture is hot.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of the hot mixture into the beaten egg.
Add remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and dark rum. Cover and chill.
When ready to serve, stir with a wire whisk and spoon over fruit.
Serves 4.
Low-fat.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, carrots, onion and pepper in water until tender. Do not drain.
Make a white sauce of oleo, flour and milk (will not be thick).
Beat in Cheddar cheese soup and diced ham.
Combine all together and heat.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and oil thoroughly; add an egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; fold in pecans.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt in microwave on High until melted.
Stir occasionally.

title: all day roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Put uncovered roast in pan and cook:

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Mix until smooth.
Makes 1 1/2 cups, which is what is in a 14 ounce can of Eagle Brand sweetened milk.
Store in refrigerator overnight to thicken some.

title: prune nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil slowly; add soda to milk and combine.
Add prunes and 1 cup flour.
Beat eggs in mixture.
Add rest of flour (1 cup), spices, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter filling
directions: Melt oleo and mix with peanut butter.
After melting good, mix in powdered sugar and mix thoroughly, kneading with hands to make it smooth.
Roll into balls and dip in chocolate or use in molds.

title: maxine's marinara sauce
directions: In hot oils, saute onions, carrots and garlic over low heat until very tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pasta. Simmer, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 cups. Serve over pasta.

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain.
Shake over low heat until dry.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream in mixer bowl.
Add hot potatoes, 1 at a time, mixing until smooth after each addition.
Add green onions, salt and pepper.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, almond flavoring, salt and eggs in mixer bowl or blender container.
Beat or process until smooth and well blended.
Stop mixer frequently to scrape bowl with rubber spatula.
Pour into crumb pie shell; smooth top.
Bake in a preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift in ungreased square pan or Pyrex dish flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix with fork until well blended.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and water.
Mix with fork, but do not beat.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost the top of cake or sprinkle with 10x sugar.
Cut right in pan.

title: pumpkin loaf bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk, eggs and oil in a bowl.
Beat well; add dry ingredients and mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Spread in a well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch). Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
It is done when it springs back when touched lightly.
Cool 5 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: creepy crawley spiders
directions: You mix all marshmallows. Then you melt chocolate until melted completely. Pour chocolate over the marshmallows. Then you drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper to make 24 clusters. Then for each marshmallow you cut 8 short pieces of licorice. Then you stick licorice for legs while it is wet or assorted candy for eyes while wet. Then you let stand at room temperature or put in the refrigerator in airtight container.

title: super bowl dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of glass pie dish.
Spread on chili; top with Cheddar cheese.
Cover with wax paper and microwave for 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: easy brisket
directions: Mix soup, ketchup and chili sauce together and pour over brisket (can do this the night before and put in refrigerator). Cover and bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in baking dish.
Place chicken, skin side down, on top.
Cover tightly.
Cook 1 hour at 350° or until chicken is done.

title: broccoli pie casserole(delicious)
directions: Grease pan. Saute onions in frypan in oil. When yellow, add flour, dissolved in 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil until thick and blended. Take off burner and add Velveeta cheese, cut up and melt on stove (slow burner). When melted, beat eggs and broccoli together. Add this to frypan. Turn into a pie plate or casserole dish. Top with flavored breadcrumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: spud dunkers
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Measure sugar, shortening, salt and instant mashed potatoes into a mixing bowl.
Add hot milk and stir to moisten instant mashed potatoes and melt shortening.
Add eggs and 1 cup of flour.
Beat until smooth and cool to lukewarm temperature.
Add softened yeast and mix well.
Add enough flour to make a soft ball of dough.
Shape into a ball in bowl by pushing dough from sides with fingers, dipped in shortening. Cover and refrigerate overnight (if you prefer, all dough to rise without refrigeration).
Remove dough from refrigeration and punch down.
Let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Roll on lightly floured surface to 1/2-inch thick and cut with a doughnut cutter.
Arrange on a warm place until dough doubles in size.
Fry in 375° deep fat until brown, turning once.
Drain and glaze with powdered sugar icing.
Yields 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: brown sugar drop cookies
directions: Cream together eggs, brown sugar and shortening.
Put sour cream in a bowl. Add soda, flour, baking powder, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Add other mixture and mix well.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Make into the size of walnuts.
Press with fork dipped in flour. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chili and cheese easy enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain. Add taco mix and cream of mushroom soup. (May stir in 1/2 cup water.) Heat tortillas in damp cloth in microwave for 1 minute or heat by dipping in hot cooking oil. Heap mixture on tortilla; add cheese and roll up. Place into 9 x 12-inch baking dish or pan.
Cover with heated chili. Add remaining cheese and onion to top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix all white ingredients together (fold, do not use mixer). Mix pint of strawberries into strawberry glaze.
You should have 2 bowls (1 white mixture and 1 with red mixture).
Take your angel food cake and pinch off little bite-size pieces and put into bottom of container, then put 1 layer of white mixture, then red mixture.
Repeat same routine, ending with red mixture on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and Parmesan cheese together. Add dip mix.
Cut beef into small pieces.
Add 1/2 of meat to cheese mixture.
Form into cone shape and add almonds or form into ball and coat outside of cheese ball with remaining beef.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins. Cool, peel and shred coarsely. Combine cheese, melted butter, sour cream and seasonings.
Fold in potatoes.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini cakes
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Melt some butter in a skillet. Spoon batter into skillet.
(Two tablespoons heaping makes a nice size.)
Flatten with spatula.
Cook over medium heat until brown on both sides.
To serve, top with tomato sauce and shredded cheese if desired.

title: tuna ball
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix ingredients together.
Shape into a ball. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix boiling water, dates and soda.
Add sugar, eggs, flour, cinnamon, cherries, candid fruit, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: lite veggie dip
directions: Mix 3 ingredients together and chill.
Stir before serving.

title: applesauce casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine rest of ingredients in second bowl.
Combine second bowl into first bowl.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Contains 157 calories per muffin.

title: cranberry nut bread(club member: brandi cook)
directions: In saucepan, combine cranberries and the 1/2 cup sugar.

Cook until sauce bubbles, 8 to 10 minutes; drain. Grate peel of orange and squeeze juice into measuring cup. Add peel and enough water to make 3/4 cup liquid. Add mixture to dry ingredients with Crisco and eggs. Fold in nuts and drained cranberries. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with softened cream cheese.

title: baked stuffing pumpkin
directions: Cut top of pumpkin to make a lid.
Remove seeds and strings. Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter until onion is clear.
Combine sauteed vegetables with rice, bread, apples, chestnuts and seasonings in bowl.
Add melted butter and enough stock to moisten, not soak, the stuffing.
Pack loosely into pumpkin, replace lid and bake on oiled sheet at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until fork-tender.
Transfer cooked pumpkin to a platter. Slice into wedges, like a cake, and serve with gravy.

title: norweigan pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Put in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; cool.
Mix whipped topping and pineapple; spread on cooled pie.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: taco ring
directions: Place crescent rolls, large end together, in a circle on pizza pan or stone. Cook hamburger, taco mix and onion. Spread over crescent roll. Top with cheese. Wrap small point of roll over hamburger mixture. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and salsa.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Break buttered toast into pieces; place in bottom of buttered dish or pan.
Beat eggs; add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread; add raisins and nutmeg.
Bake in preheated 325° oven until firm (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Soak pickles in ice water for a little more than half an hour. Wipe dry and slice into rings. Alternate layers of pickles, sugar, spices and garlic in a large earthenware bowl. Pour vinegar over mixture. Let these stand three days. Stir every morning with a wooden spoon. Refrigerate until you're ready to eat them.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix all together.
Use dip for strawberries, grapes, cantaloupe, etc.

title: squash bake
directions: Cook squash in lightly salted boiling water for 3 or 4 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain well.
In a skillet, saute onion and carrots in butter until tender.
Combine onion and carrots with soup, sour cream and 1 1/2 cups croutons.
Add squash and mix lightly.
Spoon into a lightly greased baking dish (2-quart).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or heated through.

title: nacho crab delites
directions: Place nacho chips on cookie sheet.
Slice crab meat into thin slices and cover chips with crab (cut crab approximately the size of chips).
Slice Monterey Jack cheese in thin chip size slices and place over crab meat.
Broil in oven under broiler until cheese melts and/or chips begin to turn brown.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix and pour in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: pineapple shaker snack
directions: Pour milk into a leakproof 1 1/2-quart container.
Add pudding mix and crushed pineapple.
Cover tightly; shake vigorously for at least 45 seconds.
Pour at once into dessert dishes.
Pudding will be soft-set and ready to eat in 5 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip topping.
Makes 6 servings or 3 cups.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Put 1/2 cup pecans in each pie shell.
Blend cream cheese with confectioners sugar.
Stir in blueberries.
Put 1/2 of cream cheese, sugar and blueberry mixture into each pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: strawberry angel food cake(low-fat)
directions: Slice top of cake off all the way around and remove.
Use a sharp knife and cut 1/4 to 1/2 inch in from center downward.
Be careful not to push knife down through the bottom of the cake.
Do the same from the outside of the cake.
Use your fingers and pull out the cake between your cuts.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Mix together all ingredients until creamy. Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving; the longer, the better.
Serve with corn chips or crackers.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine soup, salad dressing, milk and cheese.
Blend well. Stir in tuna, peas, noodles and onion.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: iowa ham balls
directions: Mix and shape into balls (can be made small for buffet or large for main meal).
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over balls and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
These can be frozen and sauce added when ready to bake.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Clean chicken and cut into 8 pieces; heat pan to medium temperature.
Add butter, onion and garlic.
Leave in pan until they get yellow.
When done, take out; fry the chicken in the same pan until they get gold and red.
Put in onion, garlic, parsley and tomato.
Add 3 cups of water and spice.
Shake the pan, then cover and put on low temperature for 60 minutes.

title: better than sex or coconut and pineapple
directions: Prepare cake mix by package directions.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Remove from oven and punch holes with toothpick.
Mix pineapple and sugar over low heat. Pour over cake.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip and sprinkle on coconut.

title: arkansas dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Use half to line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix together in a large bowl other ingredients and pour over cookie crumbs.
Top with other half crushed cookies. Must be refrigerated.

title: just delicious cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Shape into balls on cookie sheet.
Dip a fork or glass in sugar and flatten each cookie. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Serve with crackers (snacks).

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Mix milk and pudding together.
Then add Cool Whip to the pudding mixture.
Blend the two mixtures together.
Crumble cookies.
Layer the ingredients in a flower pot starting with the cookies, then pudding, then cookies, etc., ending up with the cookies on top.
Happy Gardening!

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburg; drain fat and put aside.
Chop up lettuce.
Slice olives; chop tomatoes.
(Mix Ranch dressing ahead of time as directed on package.)
Mix all ingredients except taco seasoning and salad dressing.
After mixing, add seasoning and dressing; then crunch up Doritos and add last.

title: guacamole
directions: In blender container, place all ingredients and blend until smooth.
Serve with chips or on other Mexican dishes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add beaten egg yolks; add flour, baking soda and milk, then add coconut and vanilla and fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake springs back.

title: lemon bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given in greased 1 1/2-quart boiling dish.
Place casserole in shallow pan of water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Serve warm. Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mini burritos
directions: Blend sour cream, cream cheese and chilies.
Spread on tostada shells; roll and wrap individually.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into approximately 1-inch pieces and serve with salsa.

title: my chocolate gravy(by the "just however much" recipe of linda (mrs.  neal) clark)
directions: Mix well the dry ingredients (sugar and cocoa).
Pour milk in skillet and melt butter with milk; add vanilla and sugar and cocoa mixture, stirring together with milk and butter mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, over low heat to prevent scorching until desired thickness.
Yield:
about 12 servings.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion.
Cook broccoli.
Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients. Bake in a greased casserole dish for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean oriental
directions: Cook beans in boiling salted water.
Drain and set aside. Melt butter in frying pan.
Add onion, bean sprouts and sliced chestnuts.
Cover pan and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Arrange half of green beans in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, spread with 1/2 the bean sprout mixture.
Combine the soup with milk; spoon half of it over vegetables.
Repeat layers of bean sprouts, soup and green beans.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl; let rise 1 hour.
Don't knead.
Cover to keep warm.
Remove and divide into thirds.
Flour board or table lightly.
Roll as thin as noodles.
Spread with melted margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll like jelly roll. Slice 2 to 3-inch circles.
Put 6 in greased pie pans or larger, more in larger pan.
Let rise 3 hours; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with favorite icing.
These freeze well.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: ham rolls or sandwiches(yields 12 to 15)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well; spread on halves of small kaiser rolls.
Divide the ham and cheese; put on rolls.
Wrap each roll in foil; bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over the pudding, then the remaining pudding mixture and top with more crackers. Frost.
Place in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: chicken anger
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Combine whipping cream, rosemary, garlic and soup; mix.
Place browned chicken in casserole; sprinkle with mushrooms.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Soften onion and celery in microwave; set aside.
Cook rice in one pan, broccoli in another.
Drain broccoli and add cooked rice. Blend Cheez Whiz and soups in bowl until smooth.
Add rice and broccoli mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf and place in a pan.
Put 1/2-inch water in the bottom of the pan around the meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauteed chicken breasts
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour and pepper. Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.

title: stewed tomato-corn relish
directions: Drain and coarsely chop stewed tomatoes.
Add corn (well drained) and a diced green pepper.
Toss with 1/2 cup Italian dressing and basil.
Makes 3 cups.
Better after setting in refrigerator a few hours.

title: strawberry duda
directions: Cream margarine, 10x sugar and egg together.
Add all but 1/2 cup crushed cookie crumbs.
Press this mixture into a 9-inch pan (pie pan or square).
Add sliced strawberries.
Top with heavy cream or Cool Whip and top with remaining cookie crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add melted butter and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in grated peel and juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted near rim comes out clean.
Chill until center is firm enough to cut.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, milk and peanut butter.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into 8-inch greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: crab cakes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and saute onion and bread crumbs over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine with all ingredients except olive oil and flour; chill for at least 2 hours.
Shape into 8 cakes; dust with the flour.
Fry them in olive oil for about 8 minutes over medium heat until brown, turning once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in bottom of pan; lay chicken over top.
Sprinkle small dash of poultry seasoning over top.
Pour soup over and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs over grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add carrots, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use 1/4 cup of batter.
Store overnight or up to 2 weeks.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix together well and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Top each cookie with a whole pecan.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook pork slowly until fat has melted and scraps are brown. Strain.
Setting aside scraps, put 1/2 cup fat in soup pot.
Heat fat.
Add onions; cook over low heat until onions are soft.
Add potatoes; toss until well coated.
Add fish and enough water to cover.
Simmer for about 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender. Mix flour with some of the milk until smooth and lump free.
Put all the milk in a double boiler.
Mix in flour mixture; heat until very hot.
Add potatoes, fish, onion mixture, salt, pepper and butter.
Taste to see if more salt is needed.
Serve pork scraps on side or in chowder.
Serves 38 (12-ounce) servings.

title: onion and cheese chicken bake(microwave)
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Add seasoning. Roll chicken in seasoned butter to coat and arrange in dish. Cover with wax paper. Cook on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn pieces over and top with mushrooms.
Continue to cook on High for 4 minutes. Sprinkle with onion rings and grated cheese.
Cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: georgian southern fried chicken
directions: Mix salt with flour.
Roll chicken in flour.
Melt Crisco. Deep fry until golden brown.

title: special lima beans
directions: Cook and drain beans; add water chestnuts.
Heat together butter, vinegar, dill seed, salt and pepper.
Pour over lima beans and serve.

title: cinnamon bites
directions: Blend cream cheese, egg yolks and sugar.
Spread about 1 or 1 1/2 teaspoons on one side of each bread slice.
Roll up bread jelly roll fashion.
Dip in melted butter to lightly coat each slice.
Roll bread in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Freeze rolled bread slices.
While frozen, cut each bread slice into thirds and bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: turkey chili
directions: In saucepan, heat diced cooked turkey.
Stir in vegetarian baked beans; then add can cream-style corn and chili powder. Continue stirring on low temperature until heated.
Serves 2.

title: pizza mac
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix milk and egg with macaroni. Pour
into	pizza
pan.
Spread spaghetti sauce, then put rest of ingredients, leaving Mozzarella until last.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from pot and cut into small pieces.
Cook noodles in broth until tender.
Mix chicken, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup with noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and green peppers and sprinkle with 3 tablespoons salt.
Let stand 5 hours in cool place.
Drain well.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 egg and butter.
Pat into sheet cake pan. Put 3 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar into blender; mix well.
Pour over batter in pan and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: quick fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Heat fruit to boiling.
Make a batter of flour, sugar, baking powder and milk and pour over the melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour the hot fruit over the batter.
Do not stir.
Bake in a 370° oven for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Put Little Smokies wieners and barbecue sauce into crock-pot. Make sure sauce covers wieners and simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground round.
Add green pepper and onions; cook until tender.
Add mushrooms, pepperoni and Italian seasoning.
Add spaghetti sauce mix, water and tomato paste; cook until well blended.

title: geneva cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In medium saucepan place water and butter.
Heat until butter is melted.
Bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat.
Add flour all at once.
Beat until mixture forms a ball.
Return saucepan to heat.
Beat 1 minute longer. Cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating vigorously after each addition.
Blend in cheeses, salt and pepper.
In 2 lightly greased 9-inch pans arrange dough 1 tablespoon at a time, sides touching.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, Worcestershire sauce and onion soup mix together and roll into small balls; place on a broiler pan. Broil 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce in a slow cooker.
Simmer while meatballs are broiling.
Place broiled meatballs in sauce and simmer about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pecan delight(walnut pie or ritzy dessert)
directions: Combine chopped nuts and crackers (finely crushed). Use rolling pin. Beat egg whites stiff and add sugar. Fold into nut mixture. Add vanilla. Pour into 9-inch pan. Bake for 45 minutes at 300° or until golden brown. Cool and refrigerate. Top with whipped cream or ice cream before serving.

title: phyllis' brownies
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, water and egg until blended and thick.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir in by hand.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add hot mixture, a little at a time, to 6 beaten egg yolks.
Cook about 2 minutes until thickened.
Combine lemon rind, lemon juice and butter.
Add to mixture and let cool.

title: cashew chicken(a springfield tradition!)
directions: Marinate chicken in milk, water, eggs and salt for 20 minutes. In a saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in a small amount of broth; add remaining broth gradually to make a paste.
Blend in oyster sauce, sugar and pepper.
Stir over medium-high heat until sauce boils and begins to thicken.
Set aside.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat and then add the sauce. Stir well and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle cheeses over sauce mixture reserving about 1/4 cup of the parmesan cheese for last. Open crescent rolls and lay on top of the cheese and pinch seams together. If they break apart during baking, it doesn't matter because you spoon it out onto the plates. Sprinkle with remaining parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until the crescents rolls are browned. Serve with garden salad and bread.

title: loaded baked potato soup
directions: In stockpot, add first 9 ingredients.
Cook and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Combine flour and milk. Stir until smooth.
Add to soup and bring to a boil, stirring often.
Remove pot from heat and add cheese.
Place lid on pot and let sit for 3 or 4 minutes.
Stir until cheese is melted completely.
Add sour cream and stir together until completely blended.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit, then mix well.
Chill and eat.

title: basic white bread
directions: Combine yeast in 1/2 cup water; add milk and 1 cup water to yeast.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Cover; let stand for 15 minutes.
Knead dough until smooth. Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down and let rise again for 30 minutes.
Divide into 2 parts.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mix together water, yeast
and	sugar.	When
yeast
is dissolved, add oil, buttermilk and	soda
and mix well.
Add 5 cups flour and mix well.
Cover
bowl
for	several
hours	or overnight, then stir slightly
and dip out onto floured board. Form a ball with your hands and cut as you would for biscuits. Bake at 450° for 15 to
20	minutes.

title: hearty ham casserole
directions: Alternate potatoes, onion and ham in buttered casserole dish. Mix milk and soup together and pour over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package directions; drain. Combine chicken, onion, mushrooms and cheese.
Fold into noodles. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over noodles.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts into small pieces.
Stir all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar together; add well beaten egg.
Beat until smooth.
Add salt and soda to flour, add flour mixture a little at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla, chopped apples and black walnuts.
Blend well.
Bake cake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Just before cake is done, combine brown sugar, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes.
Invert cake on plate and spoon topping over cake.

title: rumfpot
directions: Serve after 3 days in refrigerator.
(Layer in jar to look pretty.)
Delicious over pound cake or on ice cream.

title: crab or shrimp salad
directions: Boil egg noodles 6 or 7 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Add crab, celery and pepper.
Season with Alpine and lemon herb.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix
cocoa, sweet milk and 1 cup sugar, boil 5 minutes. Add hot
chocolate
mixture to the mixture of eggs, butter, 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Beat well before adding to chocolate mixture.
Then
beat again after adding to hot chocolate mixture. Dissolve
soda in 3 tablespoons hot water.
Then add salt
and vanilla.
Add together.
Bake in 2 cake pans at 350° for
to 30 minutes.
Frost with Devil's Food Cake 7-Minute Icing.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Butter a 10-inch pie plate and sprinkle in cheese and bacon. In a blender, place remaining ingredients and blend for 1 minute. Pour over substance in pie plate and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool 3 to 4 minutes before serving.

title: chinese pretzels
directions: Heat oil to 385°.
Sift cornstarch with flour, sugar and salt. Combine milk, water and egg.
Stir into dry ingredients; mix until smooth.
Heat rosette iron in fat until hot.
Dip hot iron into batter and return to fat.
Cook until pretzels are delicately browned, turning once.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.

title: curried chicken and vegetables
directions: In a small saucepan, combine first 10 ingredients.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper toweling.
Skewer neck skin to back.
Tie legs to tail.
Twist wing tips under back.
Place chicken, breast side up on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Brush skin with cooking oil or melted butter.
Insert a meat thermometer.
Roast chicken, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy stir-fry chicken
directions: Chop chicken into bite size pieces.
Brown in oil in wok or nonstick skillet until done.
Add diced carrots; stir.
Add soy sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Add brown sugar; stir well until sugar dissolves.
Add some (approximately 1 cup) water and let cook 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with a little water to make a thickening.
Add to chicken mixture.
Stir well; may need to add a little more water or pineapple juice to create the gravy mixture you desire.
Serve over rice.

title: rum ricotta pudding
directions: Soak raisins in rum for 1 hour.
In a mixing bowl, beat Ricotta with a fork or mixer until creamy and light.
Add sugar and lemon peel.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and rum.
Spoon mixture into 4 sherbet glasses and chill.
Garnish with thin slices of lemon.

title: pralines(microwave)
directions: Stir together buttermilk, sugar, salt, butter and pecan halves in a 4 or 5-quart dish.
Microwave on 100% power for 12 minutes, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes until sugar is dissolved.
Microwave another 30 seconds on 100% power and stir.
Microwave another 30 seconds and then beat with an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a sheet of foil.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and remaining ingredients.
Roll in snowballs.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Roll in powdered sugar when hot and again when cold.

title: speedy baked beans with wieners
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces; cook in skillet until crisp. Cut wieners into pieces.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: carrot salad
directions: Blend soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, pepper and salt. Add chopped onions and peppers.
Add cooked carrots to first mixture.
Let set overnight or longer in refrigerator.
Will keep 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, lemon juice and apples in bowl; mix together until apples are coated.
Make crust; line 9-inch pie plate.
Fill with apple mixture; dot with butter.
Adjust top crust, cutting slits for escape of steam; seal.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.
Put foil over edges to prevent over browning.

title: dole sunny punch
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: coconut cream cake icing
directions: Mix together and frost cooled cake.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Coat chicken with a mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown well in shortening.
Place in baking dish.
Blend any remaining flour mixture with tomatoes and the next 4 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serve over warm noodles.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash and cut crosswise zucchini in 1/2-inch slices.
Clean peppers and slice 1/4-inch slices.
Slice onion thinly.
Place all in a large casserole; mix well with tomatoes and sauce.
Top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough onto round pizza pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread on top of dough.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Decorate with assorted fruits.

title: cheesy fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; cut lengthwise into 8 (1/4-inch) slices. Sprinkle with salt.
Allow to sit for 30 minutes.
Rinse eggplant slices and pat dry.
Combine bread crumbs and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Place slice of cheese between 2 slices of eggplant, trimming cheese to fit.
Dip into egg and dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Fry in hot oil until golden.
Cut French bread to fit eggplant; split in half lengthwise and toast.
Place lettuce and tomato on bread.
Top with eggplant and remaining bread slices.

title: idaho potato cream sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine potato and water.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer until tender, about 10 minutes.
Using an electric hand mixer, blend until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk and seasonings, blending until smooth.
Add additional milk for a cream sauce consistency.
Yield: 4 1/2 cup servings.

title: vegetable quiche cups to go
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
I saut vegetables before mixing them with beaten eggs.
Add cheese and mix well.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Cut onion and celery fine.
Melt butter and oleo in frying pan.
Saute onion and celery until onion is transparent.
Add cream cheese and stir to melt.
Add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Add crabmeat and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serve warm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese in a large bowl. Place into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle cheese over top. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of cheese (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: nixon-style salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Put through food processor.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: fat-free hot chocolate mix
directions: The chocolate milk mix must be Hershey's brand in order to be fat-free.
Mix milk, sugar and Hershey's chocolate milk mix together until it is well mixed.
Use 3 heaping tablespoonfuls to 1 cup hot water.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Cut cooled cake into large chunks.
Blend Kahlua into pudding. In glass trifle bowl, layer 1/2 cake, 1/2 pudding mixture, 1/2 whipped topping and 1/2 chopped candy.
Repeat layers.

title: cool yogurt pie
directions: Mix together yogurt and Cool Whip; set aside. Drain juice off of peaches and take several slices and chop up into chunks. Add chunks to mixture and pour into pie crust. Use remaining slices to decorate top of pie. Chill in fridge for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together in order. Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly and put in
a
9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight before baking.
Top with grated cheese (Cheddar). Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: spectacular chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: dill to sweet pickles
directions: Drain and slice pickles. Place in large bowl; stir in sugar and pickling spice. Return pickles to jar after sugar has dissolved.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in a large soup pot; add onions and cook about 10 minutes.
Add boiling water in which cubes have been dissolved; cover and cook over low heat until onions are tender, 15 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Add dry white wine.
Pour soup into 6 earthenware soup dishes; place toast on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Bake in moderately hot oven (425°) until cheese melts.

title: dip for nacho chips
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: sliced garden tomato salad
directions: Wash tomatoes and remove stem ends.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Arrange half the slices in a shallow serving dish and sprinkle with half the sugar, salt and pepper.
Top with remaining slices and sprinkle with the rest of the sugar, salt and pepper. Pour vinegar over top.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; cook caps in butter about 4 to 5 minutes.
Combine cheeses, mixing well.
Stir in cooked, chopped stems and finely chopped onions.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture. Place on cookie sheet and broil until golden brown.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and cook until thick. Stir in the apples.
Pour into pie shell and cover with top crust. Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Melt cheese; add rice, milk and seasonings. Combine the rest.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or microwave for 15 minutes.

title: next day mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes after peeling.
Drain and mash with electric mixer.
Add cream cheese and margarine.
Add scalded milk gradually.
Put into 2-quart buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Heat up the next day.

title: celery fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Heat oil in skillet and fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: best cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Put in greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost immediately after taking from oven.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice with 4 cups water.
Fry meat in large frying pan with carrots; add diced onion and peppers.
Season as needed with your preference of seasonings.
After meat is done and onions and peppers softened; add cooking oil, soy sauce, rice and mushrooms. Scramble eggs and add to mixture and fry.

title: lemon-lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve the lemon Jell-O as directed on package. When slightly cooled, cut in cream cheese and beat thoroughly. Refrigerate and beat once or twice when still warm to keep well blended.
Cool a little more.
Put in mold and chill until firm.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk, vanilla, cocoa and salt; boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter; beat until creamy.
Stir in oatmeal before it cools.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Allow to cool.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Add
salt,
pepper,
parsley
flakes and lemon juice to crab meat.
Combine crushed toast, melted butter, egg, mayonnaise, mustard,
milk and Worcestershire sauce; mix well with hand.
Put in
long baking dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425°
for 20 minutes.
Crumble crackers on top with pats of butter.

title: applesauce
directions: Get some toothpicks.
Get some fruit, like pears (but no skin), melon, banana, apple, grapes, small rainbow marshmallows. Cut everything up that's big into little pieces.
Put on toothpick (doesn't matter which one is first, second or third).
Eat with your fingers (not the toothpick)!

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened; do not beat or cake will be tough. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in large glass dish or 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and lemon juice (if dry, add a little water).
In another bowl, mix well sugar, flour and butter, then sprinkle on top.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fish a la captain's galley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place fish filets in non-stick baking pan. Sprinkle with white pepper. Mix green onions and tomatoes; spoon over filets, taking care to cover to edges of filets. Bake for 25 minutes. Remove from oven. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise; spoon over bake filets. Turn oven to broil; place fish 6 to 8 inches under broiler until topping forms bubbles and starts to turn brown. Leave door open and observe closely to prevent scorching (takes about 5 to 8 minutes). Garnish with parsley. Serve with rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook at 450° until light brown.
Add sauce and cook at 400° until done (about 20 minutes more).

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Cool.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Pour into 9 inch pie crust. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Do not over cook.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Cream
margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, pineapple
and coconut.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Makes 2 pies.

title: shortbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Pat dough into 2 lightly greased 8-inch cake pans, pressing with palms of hands. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately cut into 16 wedges.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Melt cream cheese and margarine together and add powdered sugar.
Put coconut and nuts in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix and pour over nuts and coconut.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Mix milk, eggs and salt.
Dip slices of tomatoes into milk mixture, then dip into flour.
Lightly brown tomatoes in hot shortening in frying pan.
Brown on both sides.
Serve warm.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Mix vegetables; set aside, then combine sugar, vinegar, oil and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain well and serve.
Very good.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugar and soda in large bowl.
Add butter, peanut butter and egg; stir until thoroughly blended (mixture will be crumbly).
Press into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges begin to pull away from sides of pan (center will be soft).
Cool completely. Top with Peanut Butter Frosting.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts if desired.
Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: peas-n-bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add cheese last.
Pour into greased casserole pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix well and keep frozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon in a mixing bowl with a lid or a qt. sized baggie.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except flour, water and beef bouillon; mix well.
Use teaspoon to form balls and fry in oleo in heavy skillet until evenly brown.
Remove from pan.

title: cheese cake (2)
directions: Mix cream cheese and 2 1/4 cups sugar.
Add eggs one at a time while mixing.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 2 graham cracker lined pie tins.
Bake at 350 for about 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and let cool for 10 minutes.
Beat sour cream and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour equal amounts on top of pies.
Bake another 20 minutes or until firm.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Best if served cool.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until brown, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares. Serve hot or cold.

title: meatball soup
directions: Shape beef into meatballs.
(You can add eggs, bread crumbs, seasoning, etc. to taste.)
In large saucepan, brown meatballs in shortening; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until done.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: cherry chews
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs with a spoon in bowl.
Stir in Bisquick, fold in nuts, dates and cherries.
Spread in greased pan 13 x 9 x 1-inch.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: First chop cabbage and onion into small pieces. Then put cabbage, onion and olive oil into skillet. Cover and cook until tender. Salt and pepper to taste. Really great with cornbread!

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Crust:
Cream peanut butter and honey and heat in microwave 20 seconds.
Add cereal and mix well.
Put into pie pan.
Chill.

title: crabbies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except English muffins.
Mix well. Split English muffins to make 24 muffin halves.
Cut each muffin half into 4 to 6 pieces.
Broil until mixture is bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: taquitos
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Grate cheese and add to ground beef along with seasonings.
Lightly fry corn tortillas, just dipping in hot grease.
(Tortilla should be soft.)
Drain.
Add a small row of meat mixture on tortilla. Roll up tightly.
Secure with toothpick.
Fry taquito in hot grease until crispy.
Drain. Dip in hot sauce or ketchup to eat.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350 for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Thaw cookie dough and press out with floured fingers on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix sugar with softened cream cheese.
Spread mixture to edges of cookie pizza.
Drizzle with thin layer of strawberry glaze.
Add fruit and chill for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: In baking pan, arrange pork chops. Place thickly sliced potatoes over chops. Pour can of cream of mushroom soup plus 1 can of water over chops and potatoes. Place onion rings over this; salt and pepper. Cover with foil. Bake at 400° until done (approximately 1 hour depending on thickness of pork chops).

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in water until tender.
Allow to cool and then peel.
Remove seed and chop.
Saute onion and celery in the butter until tender.
Combine eggplant, celery and onion in bowl and add well beaten egg and finely chopped bread and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper and mix well.
Place in a well buttered casserole and cover with cracker crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes until crumbs are brown and serve.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Break chocolate into pieces and melt over low heat with coffee.
Add cocoa.
Cool.

title: rice pizza
directions: Combine tomato sauce, oregano, garlic powder, basil and salt and pour over cooked crust.
Sprinkle with hamburger, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: pork chops with apple kraut
directions: On rack in broiling pan, broil pork chops 6 inches from heat source, turning once, until rare, 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Remove from broiler and set aside.

title: pink punch
directions: Add boiling water to jello. When dissolved, add cold water, fruit juices and sugar. Chill (can put in freezer to make slushy). To serve, pour in punch bowl and add chilled ginger ale. Makes approximately 30 (5 ounce each) servings.
Can use frozen cherries or strawberries to float.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat at high speed the eggs, Crisco and margarine until well blended.
Add sugar and extracts.
Mix well.
At low speed, beat in flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add coconut.
Turn into prepared large tube pan.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: cabbage and pepper slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and peppers into large bowl.
Combine other ingredients in small bowl and stir until sugar has dissolved. Pour liquid over cabbage and pepper and mix thoroughly.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: green chiles
directions: Wash and wipe dry fresh green chiles.
Pierce once with a fork. Place on broiler pan.
Broil 1-inch from heat.
Turn often until blistered and brown all over.
When done, let cool slightly and peel.
You can cut chile open and remove seeds, if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend well and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Fifteen minutes before done, remove from oven, drain off fat and pour ketchup over top and finish baking.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Decrease to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-cherry punch
directions: Dissolve cherry gelatin in boiling water. Add lemonade until dissolved. Stir in remaining ingredients. Yield: About 3 quarts.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Dissolve cocoa in coffee.
Cool slightly; add to butter. Blend in egg yolk.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Frosting may be thinned a little with cream for desired spreading consistency.

title: onion ring-bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add soup and 1/2 can of water over beans.
Add French fried onion rings on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oatmeal and milk. Let set to soften.
Add all other ingredients.
Beat well.
Add a little more milk if mixture is too thick.
Spray muffin pan for 12 with cooking spray. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ham glaze
directions: Carefully remove skin from ham, leaving 1/4-inch of fat. Score meat in diamond shapes, inserting whole cloves in designs. Brush meat with mustard.
Place ham in roasting pan (no rack).

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until center is done.

title: raspberry sheet cake
directions: Mix the flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, salt, soda, and baking powder.
Bring the butter and water to a boil.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to the eggs and add this to the hot butter, water mixture.
Be sure to stir quickly while adding the eggs.
Add the berries. Spread on a greased and floured cookie sheet (jelly roll pan) and bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: noodleburger
directions: This is assembled the same way as Hosomaki, except each roll is larger and contains 5 ingredients instead of 1. The size of the nori sheets is 7 x 8-inches, twice the size of Hosomaki.
To make the filling for Norimaki, prepare the following 5 ingredients:

title: holiday chicken casserole(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: Add chicken to mixture.
Mix well.
Prepare Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing.
Mix as package directs.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in shallow pan for best results.

title: streusel-topped apple custard pie
directions: Place rack in lower 1/3 of oven.
Preheat oven to 425°. Arrange apples in pastry shell.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add sweetened condensed milk, melted margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix well.
Pour over apples.

title: my sweet potato souffle(my favorite sweet potato recipe!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sweet potatoes, 3/4 stick softened butter, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs and evaporated milk.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes. While souffle is baking, melt 1/2 stick butter; stir in cornflakes, brown sugar and nuts.
Spread on top of souffle. Cover with miniature marshmallows and continue baking until set. If canned potatoes are used, use only 1/2 cup milk.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: green pepper bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Cook in Bundt pan at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Then pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 350° oven until done.

title: mexican pasta squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 9-inch square baking dish. Cook noodles according to directions, rinse and drain; set aside. Combine milk, salsa, eggs, green peppers, salt and pepper.
Stir in noodles.
Pour mixture into dish and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle cheese over top and return to oven and bake until cheese melts (about 3 minutes).
Cool on wire rack about 1 hour.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: cakes from mix
directions: In 8-inch cake pan, stir mix with egg, milk, selected nuts, raisins, chocolate or other choices.
If you use applesauce, use spices instead of vanilla.
Proceed as in every day cake recipe.

title: very basic quiche
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine with rest of ingredients. Pour into slightly baked pie crust.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until middle is set, at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put 1 can green beans in a casserole dish; add 1 can mushroom soup over beans.
Add 1 can of onions to cover soup.
Add second can of beans and cover with second can of mushroom soup.
Place in oven until it bubbles.
Remove from oven and add second can of onions.
Return to oven and let brown.
Cook at 350°.

title: kay's pizza
directions: Mix flour, yeast and water; put in bowl, cover top with olive oil; let rise for 2 hours.
Divide into thirds; put into large greased pizza pan.
Put 1 can tomato sauce on each one.
Sprinkle with oregano, Parmesan and grated Mozzarella, then anything else you want (green peppers, onions, black olives, sausage, hamburger, mushrooms, anchovies, etc.).
Bake at 350° until slightly brown on bottom.
Do not overbake.

title: coolrise bread
directions: Dissolve 2 packages yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add warm milk.
Add sugar, salt and margarine.
Stir in 2 cups flour. Beat with rotary beater until smooth for 1 minute.
Add l cup flour, beat 2 minutes.
Gradually stir in enough additional flour about 2 1/2 to 3 cups to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic (5 to 10 minutes). Cover dough with plastic wrap and towel.
Let rest 20 minutes. Shape into loaves or rolls.
Put into greased pans.
Brush surface of wax paper with oil, lay over pans.
Place pans in refrigerator for 2 to 24 hours.
When read to bake, remove from refrigerator, uncover dough carefully.
Let stand at room temperature, uncovered 10 minutes.
Puncture any gas bubbles with greased toothpicks. Bake at 400°.
Bake loaves 30 to 40 minutes; rolls 12 to 18 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled easily.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend soup mix envelope, sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: crispy surprise(makes 32)
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large saucepan, over low heat, stir together the first 3 ingredients.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add cereal, toss to coat well.
Press into pan.
Cool.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: black forest punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Divide cake in half and cut each half in 1-inch cubes.
Place 1/2 of cake cubes in bottom of a punch bowl.
Pour half of prepared pudding on next.
Dot 1/2 of cherry pie filling on top of pudding.
Spread one 8 ounce Cool Whip over pie filling to edge of bowl.
Repeat process with remaining half of each ingredient.
Cool Whip in 2nd layer may be squeezed through decorator bag for a festive effect.
Chill 3 hours to let flavors mingle.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix wet ingredients, soft margarine, soft cream cheese and dry cake mix together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Drop spoonful size drops onto cookie sheet, 2 inches apart, and bake at 350° until slightly brown on bottom, approximately 10 minutes.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Store in a cool, dry place. Use as you would Bisquick.

title: fried pie crust
directions: In medium bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Using a pastry cutter, cut in shortening until mixture has uniform consistency.
Mix cream and egg together and add slowly to dry mixture while stirring until dough holds together.
Chill overnight and have fruit cold before pie preparation.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Melt cheese and add to onion.
Add soup and broccoli.
Serve hot as a dip.

title: pohupie barbecued chicken
directions: Cut up chicken. Mix remaining ingredients and marinate chicken in the sauce overnight.
Grill or bake chicken.

title: grannie's cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Use hands to mix well.
Will be stiff.
Roll into balls, then flatten.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Dip in powdered sugar to coat.
Can be made a month ahead of time for Christmas or New Year's.

title: my grandma's sugar cookies
directions: In a deep bowl, cream the Crisco and sugar. Add eggs (unbeaten).
Mix thoroughly. Add vanilla.
Stir soda in buttermilk until dissolved and add to mixture. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead a small amount of dough at a time.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut into rounds or with cookie cutter.
Bake at 475° until lightly brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chocolate chip pudding cake
directions: Mix milk, cake mix, and eggs.
Add pudding mix, chocolate chips, and nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 55 minutes in a greased bundt pan.

title: catfish cakes
directions: Poach or bake fillets; drain and refrigerate. Flake cooled fish into a large mixing bowl. Add eggs, potato, onion, parsley, hot sauce, garlic, salt, pepper and basil; mix well. Shape into 8 patties. Coat with cracker crumbs. Heat small amount of oil in large skillet; cook patties, a few at a time, until browned on both sides. Yields 8 servings.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add eggplant and zucchini; toss well.
Then add pepper strips, salt and pepper to taste and the basil.
Simmer, covered, until vegetables are soft.
Add tomatoes and allow them to cook down with the vegetables until mixture is thick and well blended.
Serve hot or cold with additional oil and lemon juice.
Serves 4.

title: caramel cake
directions: Bake layers according to directions on box.

title: party potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes 1/2 hour.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients, cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: iguana stew
directions: Make the achiote oil by frying the achiote slowly until the oil is red.
Kill the iguana by cutting off its head.
Open the belly lengthwise and remove all the entrails and the rectum.
Cook in salted water until the meat is tender (take care not to let it get too soft).
Peel and cut in portions.
Season with all the ingredients and cook with about 1 cup water, until almost dry.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook seasoned squash with onion until tender; drain.
Add egg, cracker crumbs, cheese and mushroom soup.
Blend well.
Mix some more cracker crumbs with melted butter and crumble on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put butter, sugar and milk in saucepan and heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes and remove from stove.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
When thick enough, drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: play dough
directions: In a quart jar or bottle, mix hot suds made with soap, 1 lump of sugar and 4 tablespoons of salad oil.
Shake well.
Water color paint may be added, if colored bubbles are desired.
Blow bubbles through straws or empty wooden spools.

title: apple skillet cake
directions: May also be used with canned pineapple, drained.

title: aunt betty's donuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm milk.
Put 1 cup flour in bowl with a hole in center.
Pour yeast in and let stand 20 minutes.

title: easy sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square cake pan.
In a large mixing bowl, blend all ingredients together.
Pour into prepared pan; bake for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 15 minutes; then turn out onto rack and cool completely before serving.

title: cabbage-beef soup
directions: Bring water to boil over medium heat.
Stir in bouillon cubes until dissolved.
Add carrots, potatoes, onion, beans, cabbage and meat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until cabbage and carrots are crisp-tender.
Serves 4 generously.

title: danish coffee cake(makes 4 coffee cakes)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients as pie dough.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Add this to dry ingredients.
Mix and chill thoroughly.
Divide in 4 parts. Roll each out quite thin.
Have ready 3 beaten egg whites (with a little sugar), brown sugar, melted butter and nuts.
After rolled out, smear all over with melted butter.
In middle of rectangle, put egg whites with a little sugar.
Add layer of apricot, prune or almond filling.
Then add a layer of brown sugar.
Fold edges toward center over filling.
Put egg whites, brown sugar and nuts on top of coffee cakes. Let rise about 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° or 325° until light brown all over.

title: turtles
directions: Over low heat or in microwave, melt caramels, butter and water together.
After completely dissolved, add nuts.
Mix well.
Take off heat.
Drop by teaspoon on a buttered cookie sheet and cool. Melt chocolate.
Dip cooled candy in chocolate and place back on cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix by hand.
Make large marbles and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Brown ground turkey.
Add garlic and basil; stir.
Add pasta sauce; stir well.
In a separate bowl, combine the egg white, spinach, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Mix ingredients.
Spray baking dish with cooking spray.
Spread small portion of meat mixture in the bottom of the dish, then layer noodles, spinach mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
