Repeat layers. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pearly gates omelet
directions: Melt butter in skillet on low heat.
Break eggs in bowl, giving them a dash of salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and put in skillet. Turn heat to medium.
Stir until eggs are almost done.
Strip with cheese and cover skillet.
Cut off heat.

title: double pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 36 minutes.

title: hot crab
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a bake and serve dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Cook butter, sugar, milk and egg yolks over medium heat until thick.
Add can coconut and cook 2 minutes longer.
Spread between layers and on top of cake.

title: squash relish
directions: Cover squash, onions, peppers and salt with water.
Soak 3 to 4 hours; drain well, then combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed and turmeric.
Bring to a boil; simmer 3 minutes.
Add vegetables to vinegar mixture and bring to boiling point; put in jars; seal. Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: maggie's dinner
directions: Brown the beef and sausage.
Remove the meat from the pan, then add the celery, onions and green peppers and saute them in the drippings until the onion is transparent.
Add meat and spaghetti sauce.
Cook the rotini, drain and add to meat mixture. Spray casserole dishes or 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 25 minutes in 325° oven, covered.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese is melted and brown.
(This recipe may be halved.)

title: lemonade pies
directions: Mix all together and pour into crusts; chill and serve.

title: red cabbage
directions: Stick onion with whole cloves.
In a medium skillet, heat bacon drippings.
Blend in brown sugar, vinegar, water, salt and pepper. Add cabbage, apples and onion.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove onion before serving.

title: basic white bread(for bread machine)
directions: Measure ingredients into baking pan.
Insert baking pan securely into baking unit; close lid.
Select appropriate bread setting.
Push start button.
The "complete" light will flash when bread is done.

title: quick and easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter in top of double boiler. Sift sugar with dry milk; set aside. Stir corn syrup, water and vanilla into peanut butter mixture over boiling water.
Blend in dry ingredients in two additions, stirring until mixture is well blended and smooth.
Remove from boiling water and mix in nuts. Turn into greased 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add enchilada sauce, taco sauce, green chilies and onion.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Place hamburger mixture inside tortillas and roll up.
Place in a baking dish.
Spread the cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Place chicken in crockpot. Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add herbs and remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on low for 6-7 hours.

title: butter cream icing
directions: Mix your ingredients and whip at top speed 3 to 4 minutes until well blended.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and eggs.
Stir in broccoli and mix well.
Mix the melted butter with the stuffing mix until butter soaks into mix.
Add to broccoli mixture and stir to combine.
Put into 9 x 13 baking dish or 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain pork and beans.
Add green pepper, wieners, barbecue sauce, ketchup, brown sugar, cinnamon and bacon bits and mix.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then place cheese pieces on top and let melt.

title: great, great grandma gillard's sour cream drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Batter will be very stiff.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Grease cookie sheet. Spoon batter onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes until light golden brown.
Press top of cookie.
It is done if no fingerprints appear.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Fold Cool Whip.
Put into crust and freeze 2 hours.

title: winter salad
directions: Core but do not peel the apples.
Cut into coarse size pieces. Cut the grapes in half and remove the seeds.
Mix the apples, celery and grapes together with enough mayonnaise to lightly coat. Add walnuts and serve on a lettuce leaf.
Serves 4.

title: pearl's broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy saucepan over moderate heat. Blend in flour.
Add liquids and heat, stirring until mixture boils.
Turn heat to low.
Stir in puree, seasonings and cheese. Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors and melt the cheese.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook peas and carrots until tender; drain well.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and chill in cold water and drain again.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs and onion flakes in milk.
Meanwhile, mix meat with salt, pepper, ginger, nutmeg and egg.
Add the milk, onion and bread crumb mixture to the meat and stir lightly.
Last, stir in the cream cheese.
Form into little meat balls and place in a skillet with the melted butter.
Shake pan back and forth while browning.
This will keep the meat balls nice and round. After all the meat balls have become golden brown, pour the mushroom soup over them.
Simmer until soup is melted and thoroughly distributed.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vanilla, butter, cinnamon and egg.
Add milk, slowly, stirring constantly.
Add bread cubes and raisins. Mix well.
Pour into buttered dish.
Set in pan of warm water. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: orange-spiced yam pudding(yields 12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press 1 cup cookie crumbs over bottom of dish.
Reserve remaining 1/2 cup for garnish.
Put yams in a large bowl and beat with electric mixer at medium speed 3 minutes until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in salt, spices, sugar and orange peel.
Reduce mixer speed to low; gradually pour in half and half and citrus juices; beat until blended.
Pour into baking dish; smooth top.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs, then dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, in oven 1 hour or until pudding has puffed and a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 20 minutes before cutting into squares to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo until onion is transparent. Add mushrooms, broth and Ro-Tel tomatoes and simmer 20 minutes. While this is cooking, cook noodles in leftover chicken broth. Add more water if needed.
Drain English peas.
When 20 minutes is up, add diced chicken and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted. Add well drained noodles and peas.
Stir until well mixed.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook in 350° oven until it bubbles.
Freezes well also.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, 5 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon together.
Set aside.
Beat flour, sugar, oil, eggs, salt, juice, vanilla and baking powder together until smooth.
Place in tube pan, one layer of batter, alternating with the apple slices, ending with apples on top layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Place in buttered baking dish (1-quart size).
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: good old mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover for 15 to 20 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add 3 tablespoons butter and remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Spoon into a serving bowl; drizzle with remaining 1 tablespoon butter. Serve immediately.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Add soup and cheese. Stir in rice and broccoli.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: wiener bits(a.k.a. "swelled wienies")
directions: Cut wieners into bite size pieces.
Cover with water in heavy saucepan and boil 2 hours.
Boil until almost dry.
Mix all the other ingredients and pour over pieces; bring to a boil.
Cook 20 minutes.
"Best barbecue wieners you ever ate!"

title: old-fashioned peach preserves
directions: Combine fruit and sugar; let stand 12 to 18 hours in a cool place. Bring slowly to boiling, stirring frequently. Boil gently until fruit becomes clear and syrup thick, about 40 minutes. As mixture thickens, stir frequently to prevent sticking. Skim, if necessary. Pour, boiling hot, into sterilized Ball jars. Adjust caps. Yield: About 7 half pints.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl and set aside. Combine next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables, tossing lightly.
Cover and chill 8 to 10 hours.
Drain and serve in a lettuce lined bowl.
Serves 6.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in dry ingredients. Chill dough about 1 hour.
Roll into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Roll them in a mixture of 4 teaspoons sugar and 4 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green tomato spice cake
directions: Grind the tomatoes to make like applesauce.
Heat tomato pulp, margarine, sugar and raisins together.
Cool.
Add flour, spices, soda and salt sifted together. Add nutmeats.
Mix well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mom's lasagna
directions: Brown chopped beef and drain.
Before layering the ingredients in a baking dish, mix Ricotta cheese with the eggs and cubed Mozzarella cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In a baking dish, cover the bottom with tomato sauce, then layer alternately the noodles, meat, Ricotta mixture and tomato sauce until pan is full or you run out of ingredients.
The top layer should be noodles.
Bake for 30 minutes at 275° or until hot and the top layer is crispy.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.

title: punch
directions: Combine juices and concentrates.
Add 7-Up and ice before serving.
Makes
1 large punch bowl.

title: meat-za pie
directions: Place the meat, evaporated milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt in a 9-inch pie plate.
Mix together thoroughly with a fork.
Pat this mixture evenly onto the bottom and sides of the pie plate. Pull it up over sides and rim with your fingers and press firmly into place.
Spread tomato paste over meat.
Drain mushrooms and arrange on top of paste.
Top with shredded cheese and over this, sprinkle oregano.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° in preheated oven for 35 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add vanilla.
Save out 1/2 cup flour to pour over the nuts.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flours that have been sifted together.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked lamb and spaghetti(arni me spageto sto fourno)
directions: Wash the meat and season lightly with salt and pepper.
Place in a pan.
Dot with the butter and add 1/3 of the tomatoes.
Cook in preheated 325° oven until done (1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: white and yellow turnips
directions: In large saucepan, heat about 4 cups water to a boil; add turnips and boil 1 minute.
Drain and set aside.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add bacon and cook until bacon is almost crisp.
Add onion and continue cooking until onion is tender, but not browned.
Add the blanched, drained turnip; salt and pepper. Pour in 1 cup water.
Cover and simmer over medium high heat until most of the liquid is absorbed and turnips are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Beat all ingredients at high speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° until done.

title: creamy green beans
directions: Place beans in a microwave-safe baking dish.
Microwave on high for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Set aside.
In a sauce pan, saute onions in butter for 1 minute.
Stir in flour until smooth; cook and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in yogurt.
Add beans and pepper. Top with cheese; let stand until melted.

title: amish apple strudel
directions: Into bottom of buttered baking dish, put thick layers of thinly sliced apples.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon mixture.
In mixing bowl, sift together sugar, baking powder, flour and salt.
Into this, pour beaten egg and mix until crumbly with fork.
Spread over apples, dot with thin slices of butter and bake in a 350° oven until crust is brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with milk or whipped cream, if desired.
Ice cream is also good.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix together and pour into
unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 325° oven until firm when you shake it.

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg; beat well.
Add molasses; beat well.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add to creamed mixture; mix to blend.
Last, add hot water and beat until smooth.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; cook 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon of soda.
Pour over 7 1/2 quarts of popped corn.
Divide in several pans with sides and bake in a 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: veggie squares
directions: Spread crescent roll dough over bottom of cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
While dough is cooling, mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and
dry
dressing mix.	Pour half of your chopped vegetables into the cream cheese mixture.
Spread mixture over the dough.
Sprinkle
the
rest of the vegetables on top. Cut into squares.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut; press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over coconut and pecan mixture.

title: baked carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon coconut cake
directions: Oil and coat Bundt pan with graham cracker crumbs.
In
a large measuring cup, microwave butter until melted.
Add marmalade and 1/2 cup coconut; mix well.
Spread evenly on bottom of pan.

title: oven hash
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Place this into a well-greased casserole. Top with crushed cornflakes and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with catsup on the side.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add to zucchini mixture and blend well.
Pour batter into two (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool loaves in pan on wire rack for 30 minutes before removing to complete cooling.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 1 hour.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Mix together.
Use 1/8 cup mixture for each pound of meat you are cooking.
Brown meat; add mixture and 1 tablespoon of water. Cook 5 minutes.

title: easy homemade fruit ice cream
directions: Combine both milks; add fruit.
Pour into freezer can and fill 3/4 full with half and half.
Freeze according to freezer directions until firm.

title: hamburger potato chip casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet; stir in 3 tablespoons flour.
Add chicken noodle soup (undiluted) and 1 can of milk. Sprinkle 1/2 potato chip crumbs in bottom of greased casserole. Pour meat mixture over top of chips.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin thing dessert(good for thanksgiving)
directions: Grease 9 x 13 baking pan; preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/2 cup butter and 1 beaten egg with the cake mix.
Spread and press into the prepared cake pan.
Beat pumpkin, 3 eggs, both sugars, cinnamon and milk.
Pour over cake mix in pan.
Mix reserved 1 cup cake mix, nuts and 1/4 cup butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of pumpkin mixture.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until it tests done.

title: zippy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables or seafood.
Makes 2 cups.

title: impossible spinach pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches). Mix spinach, cheese and onions in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or one minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 (11 x 13-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, salt, oil and milk.
Beat well.
Add and mix yeast and warm water.
Add flour a little at a time.
Let rise to double.
Punch down.
Make rolls and let rise again.
To make rolls, pat dough out.
Spread with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon to taste, nuts and raisins.
Roll up and cut.
Let rise.
These can be frosted or caramelized.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 24.

title: hale and hearty triticale
directions: You will need 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and margarine.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Stir in sugars and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to oatmeal mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lee center punch
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add ginger ale and sherbet at serving time.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients and mix well. When done, they will float.
Drain.

title: cheese cake that will not fail(and you may freeze it with great success)
directions: Mix first nine ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Continue beating and add sour cream and milk slowly.
Beat egg whites and add sugar.
Fold into cheese mix and pour into an angel food tin or spring mold that has been greased with butter and dusted with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake at 260° until done, about 2 hours. When cool, invert on a serving tray and spread with whipped sour cream.
Can be served plain or with a faint sprinkling of cinnamon.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend flour, baking soda, salt, rolled oats, brown sugar, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg (optional) for 2 minutes in mixer on low speed.
Add shortening, butter or margarine, eggs and vanilla. Mix for 1 minute on medium speed.
Add raisins (optional) and blend for 30 seconds on low speed.
Portion with level No. 40 scoop (1 3/5 tablespoons) onto sheet pan.
Bake until lightly browned:

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk and pour onto melted butter.
Top with peaches.
Bake at 350° about one hour.

title: grilled mushrooms with herbs
directions: Mix oil, lemon juice, oregano, thyme and garlic in a large glass bowl.
Add mushrooms; stir to coat in marinade.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Remove mushrooms.
Cover and grill mushrooms 15 to 20 minutes, turning 2 to 3 times, until tender and golden brown.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: low-fat eggnog
directions: Whisk together sugar, flour and salt in large, heavy non-aluminum saucepan.
Add eggs and egg whites.
Whisk until smooth. Gradually whisk in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring with a plastic or metal spoon for 15 minutes or until custard coats a spoon.
Remove from heat and strain into a bowl. Cover and refrigerate until chilled, at least 2 hours or overnight.
Before serving, add vanilla, nutmeg and liquor (if using).
Pour 2 cups of custard into blender; add 2 ice cubes and blend until frothy. Repeat with remaining custard. Serve immediately. Serves 12 (4 ounce servings).
Has 2 grams of fat and 140 calories per serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice 4 cups of apples.
Place in buttered baking dish with 1/4 cup water.
Cut together the butter, flour, rolled oats, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Sprinkle some lemon juice over the apples.
Spread topping mixture over apples.
Bake in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Slowly bring sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper to a boil. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: vegetable party dip
directions: Cream the cheese with a mixer.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Serve with raw vegetables such as sliced carrots, sliced white turnips, cauliflower and celery.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 can soup, the beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Drain off fat.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat potatoes.
Add eggs and sugar.
Beat well.
Add margarine, butter and flavoring.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: molded crab salad
directions: Dissolve jello.
Let set until starting to congeal.
Add crab, pimiento, grated onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Blend well and mold.

title: chocolate buttercream frosting
directions: Beat butter or margarine, salt and one cup confectioners sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Add rest of sugar alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin frosting, if needed, for good spreading consistency.

title: super delish dish
directions: Choose the size of casserole dish that best suits you.
Saute onion; add this to bacon, ground beef and garlic.
In separate bowl, toss melted margarine on croutons; coat well.
Pour this in bottom of dish.
Mix milk, cream of broccoli soup and sour cream. On top of croutons, put meat, layer of Tater Tots and 1/2 of the cheese; continue to layer until all is in pan, then pour liquid on top.
Add remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Tastes great with salad and rolls.

title: microwave scallop melange for two
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine scallops, celery pieces and pepper squares.
Micro-cook, covered, on 100% power for 4 to 5 minutes or until the scallops are nearly done, stirring once. Drain in a colander and set aside.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, M&M's and peanuts in large bowl.
Set aside. Melt margarine, oil and marshmallows in a saucepan.
Pour over the popcorn, candy and nut mixture.
Mix thoroughly and press firmly into a well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
Let cool inverted.

title: snicker bar salad
directions: Cut up the candy bars into bite sized pieces.
Core and cut up unpeeled apples into bite sized chunks.
Place both in a serving bowl, add Cool Whip, mix well.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter together well.
Add nuts, raisins, coconut and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini and carrot bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini, carrots and vanilla to eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Fold in nut meats.
Bake in large greased tube pan or 2 small loaf pans in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Check for doneness with toothpick.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Trim fat off pork chops; salt and pepper to taste.
Place pork chops in casserole dish.
Mix rice, onion soup and beef broth and pour over pork chops.
Cover dish tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons of margarine until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and broccoli.
Add eggs.
Mix gently until blended.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cover bottom of pan or casserole dish with water.
Add one layer of potatoes; sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper and/or other spices.
Continue this procedure to your level of satisfaction.
Pour in milk.
Place meats (such as pork chops or bacon or your choice) on top and cook in oven at approximately 400°.
Check on the hour.

title: audi's cinnamon buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Pull thawed bread dough into walnut size pieces.
Fill pan in a single layer. Heat together remaining ingredients and pour over dough.
Let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes and invert on sheet of foil or you will never get out of pan.

title: super bubbles
directions: Mix and use with bubble wands.

title: cucumber fritters
directions: To cucumber pulp, add cream, flour, butter and eggs.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Batter will be very thick.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot 375° vegetable oil.
Fry until crisp and brown. Drain on brown paper.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix as directed and bake in a jelly roll pan.
When cake is halfway done, start mixing your filling.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as desired on package.
Combine all ingredients; cook in casserole dish at 350° until bubbly, about 20 to 25 minutes; after cooking for 10 minutes, sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top and continue the cooking.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat eggs well; add to sugar and oleo mixture until blended.
Mix in flour, then add lemon extract, mixing well.
Fold in pecan halves.
Pour into 2 sprayed loaf pans.
Bake for 75 minutes in a 300° oven.
Cool on rack 5 minutes before removing from pans.

title: vegetarian cashew chili
directions: Cook celery, green pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Melt butter in.
Add spices, herbs and salt.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
Add beans.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cashews over chili when serving, if desired.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour into dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: chupe de mariscos(shellfish)
directions: Boil various shellfish for 30 minutes and reserve the water in which they were cooked.
Fry onion in 2 tablespoons of butter and paprika.
Add bread crumbs, milk and a little of the liquid from the shellfish.
Simmer until the consistency of sauce.
Add soft cheese, 1 tablespoon butter, egg yolks, salt, pepper and cayenne. Place the shellfish in the bottom of a clay casserole.
Pour the sauce over the top and bake, covered, in a moderate oven for 40 minutes.
Place uncovered under the broiler for the last 10 minutes.
If desired, top with hard-boiled eggs and mashed potatoes.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend well and chill.

title: microwave honey chicken
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Microwave 1 stick butter on High in a shallow baking dish for 1 minute or until melted.
Arrange chicken in single layer in butter, turning to coat each piece.
Microwave for 10 minutes on High giving dish a 1/4 turn twice during cooking.
Prepare butter-honey sauce by melting 1 stick butter for about 30 seconds on High and add honey and lemon juice to butter.
Pour sauce over chicken and microwave for 10 minutes at 80% power.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: calico salad
directions: Wash kidney beans and drain all the beans.
Add onion. Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: yummy yam balls
directions: Cook potatoes; drain.
Peel and mash.
Add sugar and crushed pineapple (drained).
With large marshmallows cover with sweet potato mixture.
Roll in coconut and place in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until coconut is toasted and the marshmallows begin to burst open.
Can be made ahead and baked later.

title: uncle ken's easy hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic.
Add all remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour covered.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust according to directions on box. Set aside 3/4 cup of mixture to sprinkle on top of cheesecake. Press remainder in 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
It will fill level full. Combine Jell-O with boiling water and chill slightly.
Combine sugar with cream cheese.
Whip chilled Carnation mix until it is the consistency of whipped cream.
Add chilled Jell-O, cream cheese and sugar to whipped Carnation and whip until thick.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top and chill until set.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in long glass pan.
Put in oven and melt.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and mix. Put peaches in pan and bring to a boil.
Pour peaches into the glass pan of melted butter.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: easy cherry crisp(microwave)
directions: Arrange cherry pie filling in 8-inch square glass baking dish. Sprinkle with cake mix and dot with butter. Combine nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Sprinkle over top of cake mix and butter.

title: unfried chicken
directions: Preheat oven 400°.
Coat baking sheet with cooking spray (Pam), coat well.

Place chicken in ice water. Put all dry ingredients into plastic bag. Shake well to mix. Roll chicken in yogurt to coat well. Transfer to dry ingredient bag. Shake well to coat. Place on baking sheet and spray with Cooking spray (Pam). Bake for 1 hour, turning every 20 min. Serve hot or a room temperature.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1/3 cup of cocoa mixture in a mug of hot water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Mix remaining ingredients except butter in casserole dish.
Add cooked broccoli and then add butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: hamburger pasties
directions: Soak crumbs in milk; add remaining ingredients except chili sauce; mix well.
Pack into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan to shape.
Invert on shallow baking pan.
Score loaf diagonally with handle of wooden spoon.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour. Fill scored marks on top with chili sauce.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
This will make 6 to 8 servings.

title: no tomato chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, chilies, half the cheese and half the olives. Divide mixture into two bowls.
Add chicken to one bowl, setting other bowl aside.
Use chicken mixture to fill tortillas.
Fold and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, seam side down.
Pour remaining soup mixture over all.
Top with remaining cheese and olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Let
mixture
of first seven ingredients get thoroughly heated.
Then
add
a
pint of cucumbers cut into thin slices. Just
before
reaching
the boiling point, pack into a jar and seal while hot.

title: grape surprise
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water, pineapple (not drained) and blueberry pie filling.
Let jell in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Spread on Cool Whip. Serves 12.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients. When mixed good, spoon into graham cracker crust. Freeze until ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening and sugars. Add water, eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture. Stir until blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a separate bowl.
Mix into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wild west beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. The last 15 minutes, put grated cheese on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Make a sauce of fat, flour, milk and seasonings.
Add corn, egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into a baking dish and cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (350° to 400°) for 10 to 30 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order.
Cover and refrigerate.
Tastes better if made in advance.

title: oven poached salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine carrots, onion and parsley in a pan large enough to accommodate fish in one piece.
Place fish on vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and allspice.
Pour wine and water over fish. Bring to boil over high heat.
Butter foil square on one side and crimp over fish or cover with sheet of buttered parchment; cut vent hole in center of covering.
Bake 25 minutes or until flesh is opaque at center when tested with skewer or fork.
Cool fish in cooking liquid.
Remove with slotted spatula and place on plate. Discard vegetables (or freeze with stock for future use in soup).
Serve salmon with one or more toppings.
Sprinkle capers on fish and garnish with olives. Serves 6 to 8.
Leave a small amount of liquid under fish on serving platter.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into small balls, flatten with fork on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let ingredients come to room temperature.
Mix thoroughly (use hands).
Form into ball (may have to chill first).
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, grapes and walnuts.
Turn fruit mixture into a romaine lined salad bowl; chill.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown the ground chuck and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste. Drain well. Drain all liquid from kidney and butter beans.
Do not drain baked beans.
Mix beans all together.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Mix in browned meat.
Place in a large baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or put in crock-pot and cook on high for 2 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour and salt.
Beat eggs thoroughly. Add milk and other ingredients.
Melt margarine in Pyrex dish. Pour mixture in dish and bake 40 minutes at 340°.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Crumble all bread in 4 1/2-quart bowl.
Soften with broth from chicken.
Add pepper, onions, beaten eggs and melted margarine. Mix well.
Add chicken, stir well. Bake in large Corning Ware dish (about 10 x 15-inch) at 350° until light brown.
Can be put in 2 casserole dishes and freeze one for later use.

title: crab-shrimp salad
directions: Boil crab meat 5 to 7 minutes in 1 1/2 to 2 cups water, lemon juice and Old Bay seasoning.
The last 2 minutes, put in shrimp. Mix together remaining ingredients with macaroni.
Add drained crab meat and shrimp.
Chill well and serve.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients; beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hobo beans
directions: Adding extra green beans makes it better.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and ReaLemon juice.
Mix well and pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream and return to oven for 5 minutes. Chill and top with cherries.

title: pepper casserole
directions: Dice peppers and onion.
Boil until tender and drain.
Add soup, milk, crackers and cheese (save some crackers and cheese for top crust, if desired).
Pour into baking dish and bake at 400 degrees until bubbly and brown.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple and add other ingredients. Sweeten cream and beat until stiff. Fold into other ingredients. Refrigerate until well chilled.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and let sit 3 minutes. Measure 2 cups water into mixing bowl.
Add yeast mixture, salt, margarine, molasses, dry milk and wheat germ.
Mix thoroughly.
(If using egg or honey, add now.)
Add both flours while mixing on low speed.
Mix dough 5 to 7 minutes on low until it pulls away from sides of bowl.
(Dough is best when soft and pliable.)
Let rise in warm spot about 1 hour.
Shape into 3 loaves and place in 3 greased loaf pans.
Let rise again.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade bubble bath
directions: Mix equal parts of ingredients and add 1/2 cup to tube of water.
Don't forget your rubber ducky.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss with remaining ingredients; chill well and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Mix cherries, sugar, pineapple and flour.
Cook until thickened.
Dissolve jello and stir into mixture while hot. Cool.
Then add vanilla, nuts and bananas.
Pour into crust. Chill and serve.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix well and cook at 350° for about 25 minutes or until good and brown.

title: slumgulian(a thick soup)
directions: Brown beef and drain it.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for a short time.
Serve hot.

title: brown frone cake
directions: Cook raisins.
Drain well and cool.
Cream butter; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs.
Alternate flour and milk.
Add soda, cinnamon and cloves to flour.
Add raisins last.
Bake in tube cake pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry forgotten torte
directions: Frost with cream.
Chill until serving time.
Slice and serve topped with strawberries.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: preston's mexican fiesta
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Add no bean chili. Continue to microwave, mixing frequently.
Pour chili mix over Tostitos chips.
Top with salsa and serve.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Saute sausage until light brown.
Set aside in a bowl for final mixing.
Saute onions in oil until translucent.
Add celery and saute until soft.
Mix sausage, onions and celery together, then add eggs.
Sprinkle Romano cheese on mixture, then add Pepperidge Farm stuffing to mixture.
Add bouillon if mixture is too dry.
You don't want it runny, but you do want it wet.
Cook in turkey.
If you prefer to cook it outside of the turkey, bake it in a baking dish for about 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O and water and let cool.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas to mixture.
Spread 1/2 in and chill.
When chilled spread sour cream over mixture and layer second half of strawberry mixture over the top.
Chill well.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Grease a long loaf pan.
Pour boiling water over quick oats. Let stand for 20 minutes.
Mix margarine, sugars and cream together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add oat mixture and dry ingredients.
Bake in long loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal celery slaw
directions: Mix last seven ingredients with a whisk and pour over celery and carrots.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot beer bread
directions: Mix all together.
Put in loaf pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: turkey and noodles
directions: Saute the chopped onion in the butter.
Add the turkey, paprika, sour cream and soup.
Blend and heat thoroughly.
Cook the noodles in salted water for 10 minutes.
Place the noodles in a pan or casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and sesame seed.
Pour turkey sauce over noodles.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add beans and chili mix.
Mix together well.
Add chopped tomatoes and tomato sauce. Add water.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: basil salad
directions: Roast pecans and croutons in oven at 350° for a few minutes. Add to salad and toss together.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and fresh black pepper.

title: yogurt pie or ice cream pie
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix together with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mint chocolate brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat first 5 ingredients until smooth. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Top will still appear wet.
Cool.

title: honey chicken
directions: Wash, dry and skin chicken.
Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken in mixture to coat both sides.
Arrange meaty side up in a single layer with sauce over it.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Roll chicken up in the rolls. Place in baking pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup as directed on can.
Pour mixture on top of rolls.
Bake 15 minutes a 375° or until crescents are brown.
May add Cheddar cheese to top if desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into small flowerets.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar, salt and vinegar; add to broccoli and mix well. Add raisins, sunflower seeds and onion and mix.
Make this several hours ahead and refrigerate, stirring a couple of times during the day.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups and milk together.
Put rice in bottom of large casserole dish.
Moisten rice with soup mix.
Layer chicken on top of rice.
Pour remaining soup mixture covering chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Simmer spices and onion in broth until onions are transparent. Add chicken and beans.
Right before serving add chopped cilantro. Serve in bowls over crushed tortilla chips.
Top with shredded Monterey Jack cheese.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour and sugar together. Make a well in center, add milk, egg and oil. Stir only long enough to mix. Fill a greased baking dish only half full. Bake at 425° (hot oven) about 25 minutes until lightly browned.

title: lentil soup
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes. Combine all ingredients (include tomato juice from can) in large Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Cover. Reduce heat. Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Remove bay leaf. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chili
directions: Peel the onion.
Chop into small pieces and set aside.
Brown the ground beef over low heat approximately 5 minutes.
Add the chopped onion, cook the meat and onion together for about 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes and kidney beans.
Season with salt and the chili powder and stir well (one tablespoon of chili powder gives you a mild chili flavor.
Add more chili powder if you like "hot" chili).
Simmer the mixture about 20 minutes.
Low or medium-low heat will keep the temperature about right.
Serve the chili piping hot.

title: done buttered rolls
directions: Mix butter and sour cream together.
Then mix Bisquick.
Put in 2 greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 14 to 16 minutes. Serves 6 to 12.

title: chicken rice
directions: Spread raw rice in bottom of 9 x 12 casserole dish or pan. Salt and pepper chicken parts and place on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup and water.
Pour over all; do not stir.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Bring sugar and syrup just to a boil and remove from heat. Stir in the peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the butterscotch chips and chocolate chips and spread on top.

title: finger jello
directions: Let set until firm, cut in pieces and eat with fingers.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Whip together and place in graham cracker pie crust.

title: marie sells' gumbo
directions: Once roux is brown, transfer roux from skillet to deep pot. While heating, add green onions, onion, celery and okra to roux and saute for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 quarts water and tomatoes.
Add shrimp or chicken and 3 to 4 bay leaves.
Cook 1 hour.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix warm water and yeast together; let stand.
In medium saucepan melt butter.
Add sugar, milk and salt.
Heat until warm, not hot.
Add yeast mixture to milk mixture in a large bowl.
Add egg.
Beat in 3 cups flour until smooth.
Add 3 more cups flour. Pour on pastry cloth and knead 5 to 8 minutes.
Let rise until double in size.
Knead again, make rolls and put in greased pan. Let rise; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Place half the Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese and butter together.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla together.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Place in pan over first half of Oreos.
Cover with remaining Oreos. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cracklin' bread
directions: Soak cracklins' in 1 cup warm water and let get soft (about 5 minutes).
Mash them in the water to get them into smaller pieces. Add corn meal and salt (if sticky, add more corn meal).
Put in greased pie pan and cook at 350° until nice and brown.

title: kahlua coffee
directions: Put Kahlua in coffee.
Top with Cool Whip.
Oooh good.

title: delicious beef and noodles
directions: meat with salt, pepper, garlic powder and flour. Heat cooking oil in heavy skillet or Dutch oven. Add meat and brown; drain. To the meat in the skillet, add broth, and simmer for 5 or 6 hours until meat is tender. Stir in soup. Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain. Add to meat with Milnot. Taste and add salt and pepper as needed. Stir well until blended.

title: cioppino
directions: Saute onion, parsley, green pepper and garlic in olive oil. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Simmer for 1/2 hour covered.
Stir in wine, seafood and basil for another 1/2 hour or until done.
Serve with hot French bread.

title: grandma taegel's chili sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Put into hot clean pint jars and seal.

title: cranberry-pineapple molds
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon peel and juice, cheese, mayonnaise and salt; beat well.
Chill until mixture begins to set and is rather lumpy.
Beat until fluffy and smooth.
Gently fold in cranberry sauce, pineapple, celery and pecans.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender; dip into cool water.
Peel off skins. Combine remaining ingredients to make syrup.
Pour over beets and bring to a boil.
Put into sterilized jars and seal (6 pints).
(I usually hot water bath these for 15 minutes.)

title: breakfast hash
directions: Cook potatoes in oil until done (do not brown). Add ham or Spam.
Beat
eggs
slightly
and
pour
over
potatoes. Add cheese and stir. Cook until eggs are done.

title: carrots
directions: Clean carrots; cut 1-inch long diagonally.
Cook until tender in salted water.
Cool carrots; add raw pepper and raw onion.
In a separate pot, boil soup, oil, vinegar, salt and black pepper. Add sugar to pot.
Boil until dissolved; pour over vegetables. Cool.
Refrigerate.

title: clay you can eat!
directions: Mix peanut butter, milk and sugar.
Add corn syrup slowly and mix.
Mold clay into shapes.
Decorate with raisins and nuts.

title: diabetic fruitcake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a lightly oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: butter lemon squares
directions: In large bowl beat butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar until creamy.
Add 2 cups flour.
Beat until blended.
Spread evenly in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour; mix well (batter will be thick).
Add Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt, pepper, onion and green pepper.
Add zucchini; mix well. Let set for a while, stirring now and then.
Heat 1/2 inch oil in frying pan.
Spoon or pour batter into pan to size of small pancakes.
Flatten out.
Brown on both sides.

title: country herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a 13 x 9 baking pan arrange chicken. In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; brush on chicken. Bake 45 minutes.

title: pizza pie
directions: Brown beef and drain grease; add salt and tomato paste.
Dice onion and pepper; add to taste.
Pour mix into pie crust.
Pour cheese onto top; place into preheated oven (350°) and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until cheese is brown.
Slice and serve.

title: shrimp curry rice salad
directions: Combine onion, oil and curry powder in a large bowl; stir in rice and mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
This salad keeps well and can be made a day ahead.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender.
Add celery salt to taste and a small amount of green food coloring.
Refrigerate and serve cold.
Nice served with chopped chives on top.

title: favorite ebert salad dressing(serves 6)
directions: This dressing also very good on finely shredded cabbage, green pepper and onion.

title: airport frosting
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening, then add vanilla.
Slowly add milk.
Stir until fluffy.

title: baked breakfast
directions: Beat eggs, salt, mustard and milk as for scrambled eggs.
Cut bread into pieces.
Mix cheese, bread and ham.
Add eggs mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: mitzi's stuffing
directions: Chop celery and destring.
Simmer with sausage meat, broken up, until soft and cooked.
Drain grease.
Let cool.

title: sauce for cucumbers
directions: Put in a jar with enough milk to make it thin and creamy. Shake until all lumps are gone.
Pour over 2 or 3 thinly sliced cucumbers.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour melted butter.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Chill.
Form into small balls, about 1 inch, and chill again.
Melt 1/2 inch paraffin and chocolate in double boiler over boiling water.
Remove from heat. Using toothpicks quickly dip balls into chocolate to cover.
Allow to harden on wax paper.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer bananas and vanilla wafers and then pour over ingredients in dish.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pour drained crushed pineapple.
Pour pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over for third layer.
Top with nuts and dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Store in sealed container. Shake before using.

title: layered rhubarb cake
directions: Layer in greased 9 x 12-inch pan as follows:
rhubarb, dry jello, sugar and mini marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix and spoon over all the layers.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour or longer.
Let cake set in pan so jello can cool.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions, salt, pepper and garlic; drain. Spread on cookie sheet and top with mushroom soup and Tater Tots. Heat in 350° oven until it bubbles (20 to 30 minutes).
Add cheese when almost done and let it melt.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Add other ingredients. Reserve 3 to 4 tablespoons of dressing for top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: easy peach dessert
directions: Pour peaches into buttered casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over peaches.
Bake in 350° oven until crust is golden brown.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Heat oil (1/2-inch) in skillet to 375°.
Mix zucchini, cheese, parsley, garlic, egg, salt and pepper.
Stir in Bisquick or Jiffy mix.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, about 1 minute on each side.
Drain.
Makes approximately 1 dozen patties.
Can substitute shredded carrots for the zucchini.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add to chili beans.
Brown onion slightly and add (may brown with meat).
Add ketchup and A.1. sauce.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes on medium.
Spoon into bowls and add shredded cheese.

title: jumbo pasta shells
directions: Cook and separate pasta shells (do not rinse).
Fry 1 pound ground beef and drain.
In a separate bowl, mix together ground beef, Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta or cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Then stuff shells with mixture; cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: yummy chocolate dessert
directions: Cream together and press in bottom of 19 x 13-inch at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift together first two ingredients.
Cut in butter until dough clings together.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Beat eggs, sugar and lemon juice until thick and smooth.
Sift flour and baking powder, stir into egg mixture.
Pour over crust and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, water and egg whites.
Beat for 2 minutes on high, 1 minute at low.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in top of cake with meat fork.
Pour cream of coconut into holes and over cake while still warm.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle with coconut.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.

title: oyster stew
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add oysters and cook 1 minute or until edges of oysters curl.
Add milk, salt, pepper and paprika.
Bring almost to boiling point and serve at once with oyster crackers.

title: creamy chocolate icing
directions: Sift sugar, cocoa and salt together in a bowl. Add flavoring and milk together in a measuring cup. In a separate bowl, using a mixer, beat margarine 1 minute. Add the dry mixture (sugar, cocoa and salt) and the milk and flavoring mixture alternately until you get a smooth texture. You may need to add more milk if it's too thick. Use this on a two layer yellow cake.

title: m. b.'s lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and place in baking dish.
Brown hamburg and onion; drain.
Place meat and rice mixture on cabbage.
Mix tomato soup and water and pour over mixture.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Batter and fry pork chops until brown. Slice onion and pull apart. Slice potatoes and place layers of potatoes, onions, salt and pepper in casserole dish. Do not drain pork chops on paper towel. Place pork chops on top of potatoes. Pour celery soup and milk over pork chops. Cover and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: creme de cacao balls
directions: Mix ingredients well; roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: cuban collard green soup
directions: Cover beans with water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let soak for at least 1 hour.
Drain through a colander.
Put beans and beef in a large kettle and cover with plenty of fresh water.
Cook until almost done.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add egg and beat.
Add dry ingredients together. Add alternately to batter with buttermilk and vanilla.
Divide into 6 equal parts.
Roll thin. Fit each into a 9-inch cake pan.
Prick with fork.
Bake each layer at 475° for 5 to 10 minutes or until medium brown.
Cool. Mash cooked fruit which has been drained.
Sweeten to taste with additional sugar.
Spread fruit between layers.
Apples, peaches or apricots may be used.
Add 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg or cinnamon if apples are used.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil for two minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Pour into jars.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: creamed corn casserole(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl combine corn and milk. Stir in egg.
Add 3/4 cup cracker crumbs, pimento, onion and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into 1-quart dish coated with vegetable spray.
Combine oleo with 1/4 cup crumbs.
Stir until crumbs are moistened.
Spread crumbs over corn mixture. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kluski noodles
directions: Mound flour on a board.
Make a hole in the center; drop in egg and salt.
Flour the board and roll out very thin.
Place sheet of dough on a cloth and let dry until not the least sticky and yet not too brittle to handle.
Sprinkle the sheet well with flour; fold into a tight roll.
Slice the roll into thin noodles; let dry longer.
Boil in salted water until they float to the top. Rinse noodles with cold water.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and pineapple. Heat until jello and sugar are dissolved. Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts. Mix well and refrigerate for several hours.

title: faccia di vecchia
directions: Poke small pieces of sardines and anchovies into dough, covering it completely.
Spread
and
press
onions
down over fish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and
pour olive oil to cover all mixture.
Sprinkle seasonings over
top.
Allow
dough to rise again (about halfway up side
of
pan)
before
baking in 375° oven until brown.
Cut
into
desired portions and serve while warm.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter and flour like making gravy.
Add milk and mayonnaise.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Good served over carrots.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: In a heavy saucepan, bring rhubarb, sugar and water to a boil. Boil for 15 minutes; cool and strain.
Stir in orange and lemon juices.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
To serve, combine 1/2 cup of rhubarb to 1 cup of soda.
Serves 24 (12 ounces each).

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburger in a large pot; drain.
Add cabbage and onion; cover and cook until onion is clear.
Add water; stir in rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for about an hour.

title: toffee
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cook for three minutes, stirring constantly. Add walnuts.
Spread over grahams on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 300°.
Immediately break apart and place on Reynolds Wrap to cool.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Over low heat, melt morsels with condensed milk and butter. Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, mix peanuts and marshmallows. Pour chocolate mixture over peanuts and marshmallows; mix together.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Bake the potatoes for about 1 hour or until fork-tender. While still warm, cut each potato in half lengthwise. Scoop as much of the inside of the potato as possible out of the shell. Reserve the shells. In a large bowl, squeeze the potato insides through your fingers to break them up as much as possible. Mix in the cream cheese, Velveeta, bacon and scallions. Mix very well. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Pack the potato shells liberally so they are heaping with the filling. You may not use every shell. Bake the potatoes until very hot. Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: chewies
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in oblong pan at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box in 9 x 12-inch greased cake pan. Cool and punch holes in cake with plastic straw.

title: mandarin orange almond salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is melted and almonds are coated.
Cool and break apart.
Store at room temperature.
Put all ingredients in bowl and toss with dressing.

title: english muffin appetizers
directions: Mix and spread mixture over English muffins.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for approximately 20 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and set aside until needed.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Mix and bake one package white cake mix in 11 x 17-inch pan. Drain pineapple.
Whip together milk, vanilla pudding mix and cream cheese.
Spread over cake.
Spread drained pineapple over mixture, then spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Serves 18 or 21.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef with 2 teaspoons taco seasoning.
Let simmer a few minutes.
Drain excess grease and chill in refrigerator.
Mix 1 teaspoon taco seasoning with dressing and chill until ready to use.

title: butter horns
directions: Blend cottage cheese in a blender or cuisinart by itself. Cream butter, add blended cottage cheese.
Cream until smooth. Add flour.
Mix till well blended.
Separate dough into 4 pieces. Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate 4 hours (or overnight).
Flour board (as for pie crust).
Roll into circle and cut (each of 4 pieces) into 16 pieces.
Roll from large end to small end to form a croissant.
Grease cookie sheet or use parchment paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost.
Best if serve warm but delicious all ways.

title: holly dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs, coconut, chips and nuts in order given.
Pour milk over all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix uncooked ground meat with the chili powder, salt and pepper.
Place meat mixture in an oblong baking dish.
Layer all the other ingredients in the order listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Line
bottom
of 3 (9-inch) greased round pans with wax paper. Microwave	chocolate
and	water
in
bowl
for
1 1/2 minutes on High until chocolate is almost melted.
Stir until chocolate
is completely	melted.
Mix flour with baking soda and
salt;	set aside.
Beat
margarine
and
sugar.
Add egg yolks,
one
at
a time.
Beat well.
Stir in melted chocolate and
vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk. Beat
egg whites until stiff, gently stir in batter.
Bake for 30	minutes
at 350°. Cool and spread on Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: baked pork chops and dressing
directions: Rub rosemary on each side of chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brown in butter or bacon drippings.
Place over dressing mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread crescent roll dough on a flat baking sheet, and pinch seams together.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until brown.
Remove from oven and cool completely. Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until blended.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Chill. Cut into wedges or squares.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients on low heat until thick; set aside.
Combine the pineapple chunks (drained), 1 cup of grated Cheddar cheese and cooked mixture.
Melt butter; add Club crackers (crushed fine) and top pineapple mixture with this.
Cook at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix the vanilla Junket and condensed milk.
Add eggs, sugar and evaporated Pet milk.
Cook until a little hard.
Put into freezer and fill up with milk.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together corn, eggs, salt and pepper, and cornmeal. Pour half of
mixture
in
buttered
baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese
and
chopped
green chilies.
Pour rest of corn mixture over this
and
add 1/2 cup grated cheese and dot with butter. Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick mix, cheese and milk until soft dough forms. Mix for about 30 seconds.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 450° until brown.
Brush with butter.
You can also sprinkle with garlic powder.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Mix slowly until blended.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Roll out and use for open fruit pies, tarts or other small pastries.
Bake at temperature required for fillings.

title: aunt ann's chicken
directions: Brown chicken on all sides.
Grease a large pan.
Place uncooked rice in the pan.
Mix and heat the soup and milk on the stove.

title: new potato bake
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, sour cream and pepper sauce.
Add potatoes and onions.
Toss to coat well.
Use a 12 x 8-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole.
Spoon potato mixture in dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° until potatoes are fork-tender.
Garnish and serve.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, brown sugar and eggs; stir in buttermilk and flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients together; stir in. Mix in pecans, dates and cherries.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop dough with teaspoon (1/2 teaspoonful), about 2 inches apart, onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with 1/2 of cherry or pecan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: goldenrod eggs
directions: Combine butter and flour in saucepan.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Chop egg whites and add to sauce.
Pour this over hot toast or biscuits.
Grate egg yolks and sprinkle on top of sauce.

title: ome rice(korean)
directions: Scramble eggs and set aside.
Cook meat, onions, peppers, cabbage, carrots and garlic until meat and onions are done.
Add rice, eggs and soy sauce.
Stir until hot.
Serve.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips with peanut butter.
Then mix in peanuts.
Next, stir in corn flakes.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix the sugar, cornstarch and salt together.
Add the vinegar and beet juice.
Cook sauce until clear.
Add the beets.
Keep beets and sauce in warm place for 30 minutes before serving.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar, flour, lemon juice and salt in a large bowl.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs, half and half, nutmeg and sugar in a medium size bowl until well mixed.
Pour over hot rhubarb in pie shell.
Bake until top of pie is browned about 10 minutes longer.
Cool completely before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh taco dip
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add onion and then add rest of ingredients.
Simmer until warmed through.
(May be made ahead and reheated.)

title: mustard chicken
directions: Mix margarine and mustard in saucepan and add flour to thicken as it heats.
Dip chicken pieces in mixture and place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil oleo, water and cocoa.
Remove from heat and add flour, sugar and salt.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and baking soda. Pour onto 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet (greased) and bake at 375° for 18 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and blend well.
Spoon into an ovenproof dish and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Mix together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla and chocolate syrup.
Add flour last.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: three-minute canned beans
directions: Bring water, vinegar and sugar to a hard boil.
Add beans; boil for 3 minutes.
Add salt to each sterilized jar.
Fill jars with beans and water.
Be sure lids are in boiling water and ready to seal on jars.
No need to pressure cook.
When preparing beans to cook, drain off water and rinse if you wish.
Then add fresh water and seasonings.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl. Prepare bundt pan or tube pan with butter. Mix sugar and cinnamon in small container and sprinkle onto the buttered pan. Pour cake batter in pan and then sprinkle remaining sugar/cinnamon mixture on top of the cake. Bake for 45 minutes until done.

title: savory microwave new potatoes
directions: Place margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Cook on High for 30 to 45 seconds.
Add potatoes, onion and pepper; toss to coat.
Cover tightly.
Cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: corn pops
directions: Put Corn Pops in a big bowl and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large pan and cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until the butter is melted.
Bring to a boil and continue cooking to the firm ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour over Corn Pops.
Mix thoroughly.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar and flour; add melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients; mix with spoon.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until custard sets.

title: spread cheese
directions: Melt cheese.
While warm add mayonnaise and stir well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into container; let cool.
Set for at least 24 hours.

title: tofu mushroom stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake potatoes for 40 to 60 minutes. Combine onions, mushrooms and sage in skillet.
Cover and stew 5 minutes over medium heat, until mushrooms become tender and release their juices.
Season with white pepper.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Mix all ingredients into a paste.
Rub on meat.
Roast at 300 degrees for 30 minutes per pound.

title: low calorie strawberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice to boiling.
Add gelatin and cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Combine flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk. Add flavoring and coconut last.
Mix; bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hong kong chicken
directions: Saute mushrooms in the oil for 5 minutes.
Add celery and green onions and cook 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except dissolved cornstarch and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir cornstarch into chicken mixture.
Simmer until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings, 250 calories per serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs; stir in. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add berries.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: dawn's nana-berries ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Pour into can; add canned milks and stir well. Add fruit mix.
Add dairy milk to fill line on can and stir. Makes 4 quarts.
Omit fruit for great vanilla ice cream.

title: good and quick jello
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in boiling water.
Add cherry pie filling to jello.
Add pineapple with juice.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well and put in container.
Add milks, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add fruit.
Stir well.
Freeze.

title: party chicken
directions: Lay beef on bottom of 10 x 12-inch pan.
Wrap 2 slices bacon around each chicken breast.
Put on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 3 hours at 250°, uncovered.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: church punch
directions: Mix in gallon container. Fill with water and freeze.
Take out of freezer about 2 hours before you serve.
Put in chilled punch bowl and break apart with knife. Add 2 quarts ginger ale.
You can add more ginger ale, if
needed.

title: smoked brisket marinade
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate brisket for 12 hours prior to cooking.

title: no-bake pineapple pies
directions: Mix condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Fold pineapple into mixture.
Add lemon juice and fold mixture together again.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with chopped nuts, covering tops completely. Chill.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Pour chopped apples in cooking dish. Pour water over apples. Add dry ingredients over apples. Cut or slice margarine over the top of dry ingredients. Cook until golden brown at 350°.

title: polish sausage with peppers and onions
directions: Cut peppers into 12 wedges.
Cut onion into 1/2-inch thick slices, then separate into rings.
Cook peppers, onion, garlic and thyme in oil in large pan 8 to 10 minutes, stirring often.
Remove to warm platter and keep warm.
Place sausage in water in pan. Cover and cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes, turning once. Remove cover and continue cooking 2 to 4 minutes or until cooked and browned.
Remove to platter and pour off drippings.
Increase heat to medium-high and add wine to pan.
Stir to loosen brown bits, then return vegetables and sausage to pan, stirring to coat with sauce.
Continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes or until sauce is slightly reduced and thickened.
Makes 6 servings.

title: artichoke chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chicken in skillet with butter. Put chicken in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Do not drain skillet of pan juices.
Cut artichokes into quarters.
Arrange artichokes and mushrooms on top of chicken and set aside.
Saute onion in pan juices; blend in flour and seasonings.
Add chicken broth and wine.
Cook until bubbly; remove from heat and pour over chicken.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is done. Serve over noodles or rice.
Garnish with parsley.

title: stuffed shrimp fillets
directions: Combine shrimp, rice, curry powder, salt and butter.
Spread between fillets; fasten together.
Put on top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Cut into small pieces.
Mix stuffing and melted margarine together.
Mix soup and chicken broth together.
In a large, greased casserole dish, layer dressing and chicken; pour 1/2 of soup mixture over them.
Repeat and top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: don't peek chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; set aside.
Mix together the rice, soups, water, garlic, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into pan.
Press the chicken into the mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake for 2 hours.
Do not open the cover (not even to peek) during baking.
Add some carrot or celery chunks or use flavored rice.
Make ahead and rewarm in oven or microwave.
Enjoy!

title: more than minestrone soup
directions: Saute bacon in large, heavy pot for 5 minutes, until crisp. Cut into bite size pieces. Add onion and celery to bacon and drippings. Cook until vegetables are soft, but not brown, about 5 minutes.

title: parsnip cakes
directions: Pare parsnips and cut in halves.
Boil parsnips in water, about 30 minutes or until tender; drain.
Mash parsnips.
Mix parsnips, flour, salt, pepper, margarine, onion and egg.
Shape into 8 patties.
If mixture is too soft to shape, mix in some of the bread crumbs until stiff enough.
Coat patties with bread crumbs.
Heat shortening in skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook patties about 5 minutes, turning until golden brown.

title: simple pecan pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender except pecans and blend for about 45 seconds;
add half of the pecans and blend for about 10 seconds and then add rest of pecans for about 3 seconds.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: tacos
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain any fat from pan.
Add onion soup mix and chili powder and approximately 1/2 to 3/4 cup of water. Turn to simmer.
Heat refried beans and top with about 2 to 3 tablespoons of the cheese and chopped onion as desired.
When meat mixture has absorbed all the water, serve and let everyone make their own tacos buffet-style.
Serves 5 to 7.

title: easy garlic rolls
directions: Divide thawed dough into 20 portions.
Shape into balls. Combine remaining ingredients; stir well.
Dip dough balls into margarine mixture and place in a lightly greased 9-inch round cake pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, for 1 hour or until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Dilute soup with 1/2 cup asparagus juice.
Melt butter; add chopped onion and carrots.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain water chestnuts and slice thin.
Make in 2 layers, ending with crushed cheese bits.
Cook about 15 minutes in 400° oven that has been preheated.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
Boil 1 minute stirring constantly.
Stir in butter, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Keep hot until time to serve.

title: fruit cake i
directions: Combine raisins, dates, figs,
brown
sugar, butter and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil and
simmer
minutes.
Cool.
Sift flour, spices, salt and soda 3 times and add to cooled mixture. Stir in nuts, gumdrops and candied fruit.
Pour
batter into Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: crunchy apple cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 8 inch square pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top.
Pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle pecans over the butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until top is brown and filling bubbles. Cut apple slices into 2-3 pieces.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order as numbered on a plate or fancy platter.
Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos!
Great for parties.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet. Add seasoning and tomato soup. Simmer 10 minutes. Add shredded cheese, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce; cook slowly until cheese melts.

Stir in rice. Cut peppers in half lengthwise. Remove seed and membranes. Cook in boiling salted water 3 minutes; drain and cool. Fill peppers with filling and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly. May add a thin slice Velveeta cheese on top of peppers before heating.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Mix 1 cup milk and pkg of unflavored gelatin (knox) together. Stir over low heat till dissolved.
Then add 4-2 1/2 oz milkyways (cut up).
Stir till smooth---add cool whip.

title: party time meat balls
directions: Add hamburg and all chopped vegetables, crushed crackers and remaining ingredients except soup.
Brown meatballs then add soup and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup margarine, eggs and vanilla together.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the hamburger and drain.
Mix in onions Mix the Ragu with the cooked hamburger.
Drain the noodles.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer bottom of pan with noodles.
Sprinkle seasoned salt on noodles.
Layer Parmesan cheese, layer sauce with hamburger, layer grated Cheddar cheese and repeat layers.
End up with sauce and cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salad medley
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: butternut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan with butter flavored Crisco.
Beat eggs until light and foamy in large bowl. With mixer, blend in sugar, vanilla and Crisco until creamy. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs to mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts at low speed (mixture will be stiff).
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut in bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: no-peek beef tips
directions: Layer ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish in order given. Put a lid on the dish or aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° oven for 3 hours and do not peek.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: strawberry shake(diet)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until thickened. Other fruits may also be substituted.

title: breakfast pie
