directions: Toss flour and cheese together.
Add eggs, milk, sausage, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg. Beat 4 egg yolks and 2 egg whites and add to dry ingredients; beat well. Add milk gradually, then stir in melted butter.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
Beat together.
Add nuts and dates. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together. Put in ginger ale just before serving.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate; add butter.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until top is firm and coconut is lightly browned.
Cool before cutting.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and shortening in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending at low speed after each.
Add flavoring.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until top is firm.
Remove from oven; loosen around edges with knife and pour topping over cake.

title: walk to school cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form cookies in balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° until done.
Grease cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Form into small balls and let stand overnight.
Melt 1 large package chocolate chips and 1/2 cake paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture with a toothpick.
Place on waxed paper until cool.

title: sugar-free applesauce cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar substitute.
Add applesauce and water.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In a large bowl, add warm water, yeast and sugar.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Add warm milk, shortening, eggs and salt.
Make a stiff dough.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and make into loaves (4).
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon in an appropriate baking dish.
Mix well. Lay bacon on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili dip
directions: Saute onions and pepper.
Add ground chuck until done, but not brown.
Add soup, tomato sauce, tomato paste and chili powder. Simmer 30 minutes.
Add cheese and cook until cheese is melted. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with the salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil and 1 tablespoon of butter in skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
(Do not cook any longer than 4 minutes on each side.) Remove from skillet to serving platter.
Add green onions, lemon, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly. Whisk in the broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: kahlua chocolate trifle
directions: Make cake according to directions on package.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make instant pudding, using 4 1/2 cups milk.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except pecans and heat for 1 1/2 minutes. Cool to spreading consistency.
(If too stiff, add a small amount of milk.)
Frost cake and sprinkle sides and top with pecans.

title: butter bud cookies
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar.
Add the well beaten eggs. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to egg mixture with vanilla.
Mix. Roll into small balls and press with fork. Place 1/2 cherry on top of each cookie.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in moderate oven until brown.

title: nell cannon's french fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut in 1-inch squares.
Drop in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; dredge with flour, then dip in egg which has been combined with milk.
Roll in crumbs or pancake flour and fry in deep hot oil 2 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick and easy rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a microwave bowl.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir thoroughly, then microwave for 3 minutes more on High.
Cool to room temperature.

title: partridge italiano
directions: Cut breasts into 1-inch pieces.
Mix flour, garlic salt, paprika, salt, pepper and rosemary.
Dredge partridge pieces in mixture.
Heat olive oil, butter and fresh garlic in large skillet.
Saute partridge pieces over medium heat, stirring constantly, until golden brown.
Cooking time is approximately 7 minutes.

title: beef stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Drain, remove stems and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Shape meat mixture into balls and fill mushrooms.
Place on jelly roll pan. Broil 2-inches from heat for about 5 minutes or until meat is brown.
Serve warm.

title: chicken pie 1
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cut chicken up into chunks and put into bottom of a baking pan.
Cut 1/2 stick margarine up on top of chicken.
Mix chicken soup with broth.
Pour mixture over chicken. Mix sweet milk and Bisquick.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick banana split cake
directions: First, cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with whole vanilla wafers.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix cake, yeast and salt.
Add water, then flour.
Let rise 1 hour.
Roll out, or drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Let rise again for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: yeast butter sweet rolls
directions: Put flour in large bowl.
Work to sides.
Mix 1/2 cup warm water with yeast; let rise.
Mix 1 cup warm milk and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Add 2 eggs if you like.
Melt lard and pour into flour. Add the yeast water, then milk and sugar.
Work all together.
Work until it doesn't stick to fingers.
Butter your bread pan, then make your rolls and let the dough rise for 1 hour in bowl, then 1/2 hour in pan.
Turn oven to 350°.
Leave in oven until done about 30 to 35 minutes.
Make sure oven is hot.
Bake, then butter the top.

title: easy garden quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray pie plate with Pam.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix well all 3 of the items in a large bowl, then pour into a graham cracker pie crust. Chill for 1 hour.

title: hamburger, macaroni and vegetables
directions: Note:
If this
is it too spicy, season "to taste" with spices.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onion soup mix, eggs and bread crumbs. Shape into
small
balls	and
place
in a shallow baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Drain and
place in	chafing
dish.	Mix
barbecue sauce, honey and Tabasco sauce; pour over meatballs.
Yields 36 meatballs.

title: beet cake
directions: Beat together oil and sugar. Add eggs, pineapple, beets and vanilla. Add soda, baking powder and cinnamon to flour.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° in tube pan or three 9-inch cake pans.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add tomatoes.
Break up with fork. Add tomato paste, garlic salt, oregano leaves and basil leaves. Bring to boil.
Stir occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan.
Reserve 1 cup of meat sauce and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in pan.
Pour 2 1/4 cups of broth over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy chicken pizza(makes 6 servings)
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels. Cut chicken into 1/2-inch pieces. In a medium bowl, combine green onions, minced garlic, vinegar, soy sauce, red pepper and first tablespoon oil. Add chicken pieces; stir to coat. Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. Drain, reserving marinade. Heat second tablespoon of oil in a large skillet. Add chicken pieces. Cook and stir until no longer pink. Stir cornstarch into reserved marinade. Add to skillet. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Spoon evenly atop the Boboli. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 12 minutes.

title: homemade windex
directions: Recipe #1:
Fill a gallon container with water and add ingredients.

title: breath o' spring salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add water to juice to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in pineapple liquid and add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Turn into lightly oiled mold and chill until firm.
Soften unflavored gelatin in cold water; dissolve in hot water.
Combine remaining ingredients, blending well.
Pour over pineapple layer; chill until firm. Garnish with salad greens.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Mix boiling water with Jell-O; add ice cubes.
Mix all ingredients; refrigerate until firm.
Goes well with meat or poultry.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hour.
This recipe will serve 20 and also freezes well.

title: crock-pot pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add spaghetti and pizza sauces.
Cook twist noodles in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and add to sauce. Layer noodles, sauce and cheese, then pepperoni (should have 4 or 5 layers of each).
Cook on high for 2 hours or on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Mix everything together with hands.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: walnut penuche(microwave)
directions: To toast walnuts, spread in single layer in a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Stirring every 2 minutes, microwave on High 6 minutes or until toasted.
Place butter in a 2-quart glass measure. Microwave on High 1 minute.
Blend in brown sugar and condensed milk.
Stirring every 2 minutes, microwave on High 8 to 9 minutes or until mixture is a medium-caramel color.
Stir in vanilla and beat with a wooden spoon 2 to 3 minutes.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square dish.
Cool to lukewarm, then refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.
Yields 36 pieces.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cut cornbread in chunks. Add pickles, tomatoes, green pepper and beans. Fry sausage, crumble, drain and add to cornbread mixture. Add enough salad dressing to hold mixture together. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple salad (waldorf)
directions: Place in bowl and toss, coating with mayonnaise.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach; pat dry and tear into bite size pieces.
Combine with mushrooms, onion, almonds and egg.
Combine oil and remaining ingredients in jar.
Cover tightly and shake.
Pour dressing over spinach mixture just before serving and toss.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together in order given.
Pour into a container with cover and place in refrigerator.
Serve with fruit or gelatin salads.
Yield:
1 1/3 cups.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Over medium heat in a medium saucepan, cook onion in butter until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat until all the cheese has melted.
Transfer to a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: 24 hour ham and pasta salad
directions: To hard-cook eggs, place eggs in saucepan; cover with cold water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat to just below simmering. Cover; cook for 15 minutes.
Run cold water over eggs until cool. Remove shells; slice eggs.
Meanwhile, in a colander run peas under hot water until separated.
In saucepan, cook macaroni in a large amount of boiling salted water according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse in ice water.
Drain again.
Set aside. Place lettuce in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole or souffle dish.
Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper.
Top with the drained macaroni.
Sprinkle egg slices with a little salt; arrange atop macaroni, standing some egg slices on edge, if desired. Layer in order atop eggs:
ham strips, peas and cheese.
Combine the mayonnaise or salad dressing, sour cream, green onion, mustard and pepper sauce.
Spread atop salad, sealing to edge of casserole.
Cover; chill in the refrigerator for 3 to 24 hours. Before serving, sprinkle top of salad with snipped parsley and paprika; toss.
Serves 4.

title: vinegar pie(1924)
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, reserving the vinegar until last.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp quesadillas
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour tortillas, together.
Place filling on one tortilla, then cover with another tortilla.
Bake at 450° for 3 to 5 minutes, until the cheese is melted.

title: hunt's burgers
directions: Hollow out center of buns, leaving bottom and 1/2-inch rim. Crumble up bread you have removed and mix well with meat, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of Hunt's tomato sauce.
Fill buns.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: *Located in refrigerator section near cookie dough, container is round and cardboard thin.
Twist and it pops open.
Container holds 10 biscuits each.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces;
brown in hot fat.
Brown onion in
fat;
add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes. Pour over
chicken.
Bake
uncovered
in moderate 325° to 350° oven for 1 hour.
Sauce may be used for meats also.
Serves 6.

title: pizza!
directions: Mix hot roll mix according to package directions for pizza. Divide dough in half.
Press onto greased baking pans.
Divide pizza sauce between both pans.
Spread cheese onto sauce, 1 bag per pan.
Divide packaged pepperoni in half, half for each pizza. Spread equal amounts of onion, bell pepper and olives onto pizzas. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(I usually bake on bottom rack for 5 to 7 minutes, then move to middle rack for remainder of baking time.)

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer all but last 2 ingredients as listed.
Then spread a mixture of mayonnaise and sugar over top.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Bake in deep dish at 350° for 50 minutes. Serve with your favorite ice cream.

title: apple bread
directions: For a perfect baked pie shell, put the crust into pie pan and set in fridge until very cold.
Set another pie pan of same size inside it.
Bake upside down in oven.
It will be perfect.
You will know when the crust is done because the edge showing will be golden.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese and peanut butter; add milk and lemon juice. Mix.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate. Grate chocolate on top, if desired.

title: hearty baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add remaining ingredients into a crock-pot and cook for 6 hours.
I usually double this.
Great for picnics.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sprite and sugar in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
It will look like a clear white mix. Remove from stove.
Mix in Jell-O.
Cut strawberries (leave a few for the top), add to mixture.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate until mixture sets up about 1 hour.
Top with whip cream and a few pieces of strawberries.

title: cherry-apple crisp
directions: Thaw cherries; do not drain.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon; add cherries and juice and apples.
Toss to coat.
Place in an 8-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle with granola.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Warm oleo.
Mix sugar and oleo.
Mix vanilla and eggs together; add to sugar mixture.
Add baking powder to flour.
Add 1/2 of flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Mash bananas and add to sugar mixture, then add rest of flour to sugar mixture. Add nuts.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake at 350°.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: cocoa and cola cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Combine all ingredients except Cola and marshmallows.
Blend on low speed.
Beat for 1 minute on medium speed.
Add Coke; blend well.
Stir in marshmallows. Pour batter in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Spread with Icing.

title: gobs
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs.
Add dry ingredients with milk.
Add boiling water and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: honey barbecue chicken
directions: Put chicken in pan.
Spread butter on top of legs.
Bake for about 10 minutes at 350°.
Then mix your honey and barbecue sauce together and coat chicken.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check and turn chicken.
Put remaining sauce on.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine cooked rice with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix thoroughly, stirring until just moistened.
Spoon into muffin tin cups.
Sprinkle each muffin with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook
carrots until tender;
add all other ingredients. Simmer until thick.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Place half the cake pieces in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Reserve 18 cherries and spoon remainder of filling over cake pieces.
Top with remaining cake pieces.
Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon over cake.
Chill 5 hours.
Cut into 9 (3-inch) squares.
Garnish each square with 2 cherries.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Sprinkle with salt.
Spread out in layer on board or paper toweling; let stand 20 minutes.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Dip each slice into the mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Heat olive oil and brown eggplant quickly.
Cooking quickly over medium heat will keep eggplant from absorbing too much of the oil.

Drain on paper towel. Continue cooking eggplant slices, adding more oil if necessary. Pour 1/4 of tomato sauce in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole. Top with 1/3 of the eggplant slices and 1/3 of the remaining tomato sauce and 1/3 of the cheese.
Continue layers.
Cover and bake in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove the cover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put
first 3 ingredients through food chopper.	Add 1/2 can crushed
pineapple.
Sprinkle
with
sugar.
Let
stand 2 hours. Add
lemon	Jell-O	dissolved in hot water.
Add black walnuts. Pour into mold and chill until molded.

title: *scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour with cornstarch, sugar and salt 3 times.
In a large bowl with wooden spoon, beat butter until creamy.
Gradually work in flour mixture.
Pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Prick with fork all over (right through until fork hits bottom of pan).
Bake for about 45 minutes, until slightly golden.
To test for doneness, take from oven and cut small piece. Shortbread should be uniform in color; no dark line appearing in the center.
Cut into squares while warm.
If desired, sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.

title: mexi-bean ensalada
directions: Cook beans in boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 8 to 10 minutes. Combine with remaining ingredients; mix well. Cover and chill several hours, stirring occasionally.
To serve, toss to coat vegetables with marinade.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: best ever banana cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and bananas.
Add chocolate.
Beat well.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add to mixture with the water. Mix well.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and brown in a little oil.
Place in shallow baking dish and cover with sauce mix (cream of chicken soup, catsup and Worcestershire sauce).
Top with onion, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburger upside-down pie
directions: Saute meat; drain off oil.
Add the Ragu sauce; add seasons and stir.
Follow directions on Jiffy mix box.
Pour Jiffy mix on top of meat sauce and spread.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in a blender.
Pour into a greased glass pie pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place half the potatoes in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with half the flour, salt and pepper; dot with half the butter.
Repeat with the rest of the ingredients. Pour milk over top; cover the baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake at 350° until potatoes are brown on top, approximately 30 minutes.
Add more milk during cooking if potatoes become dry.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients and wings in plastic bag or bowl and let stand overnight, turning wings once or twice.
Place wings and marinade in dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 8 to 12 minutes, until chicken wings are fork-tender, stirring once during cooking.

title: angel biscuits(low salt)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water; set aside.
Mix all ingredients (except yeast) together.
Add yeast and knead.
(The more you knead the dough, the better the biscuits.) Roll out on floured surface; cut with cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let set until they raise, about double their size.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Enjoy.

title: hot artichoke & spinach dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften to room temperature. Cream together with mayo, parmesan, garlic, and garlic salt. Mix well. Add the drained and chopped artichoke hearts and spinach. Mix well. Spray pie pan with pam, pour in mixture and top with mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until top is browned. Serve with chips or toasted bread.

title: hidden valley pinwheels
directions: Mix the cream cheese, salad dressing and onions.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle on the celery, pimentos and olives; then roll and wrap tightly and chill for several hours. Cut off the rolled ends.
Cut rolls in 1-inch slices.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add the milk, oleo, chocolate and vanilla.
Pour into loaf pan.
Mix the remaining dry ingredients and spread over cake batter; pour water over the top. Cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole with meat sauce
directions: In a small pan, melt margarine and saute onion and peppers; let cool completely.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, onion and peppers mixture, creamed corn and undrained niblets.
In a small bowl, combine cheddar cheese, cream of mushroom soup and milk. Preheat oven to 350 degrees; spray a 9 x 13 casserole dish with vegetable spray.
At the very last minute, stir the muffin mix into the corn mixture, using a whisk.
Stir only until the mixture is moist. The muffin mix must be added at the last moment; otherwise, it oxidizes and the casserole will not rise.
Next, spoon corn mixture into the prepared dish and spoon the cheese mixture on top.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
For the sauce, in a Dutch oven, crumble the ground round; add onion, garlic and celery salt.
Cook over a medium-high heat until browned; drain. Add tomatoes, broth, tomato paste, pepper and thyme, stirring well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add parsley; cook 5 minutes more. Cut casserole into 8 servings, spoon 1 cup of sauce onto each piece.
The sauce can be served over pasta, rice or beans.
The sauce can be stored in the refrigerator for one week or in the freezer for 3 months.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt the butter.
While it's hot, add both sugars.
Stir.
Mix the flour, soda and salt.
Beat the egg lightly, then add the egg and vanilla to the butter mixture.
Stir.
Now add the butter, egg and vanilla to the flour mixture.
Stir again, then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir until all is mixed well and put in the refrigerator for about an hour.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt onion, butter and flour together.
Add all at once, salt, pepper and milk.
Stir constantly for about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and water.
*Dissolve cubes in water; bring to boil and add broccoli.
Cook; do not drain.
Add to cheese mixture.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix well the crushed vanilla wafers, nuts, confectioners sugar, frozen orange juice and butter.
Roll in small balls 3/4 to 1-inch.
Do not bake.
Combine confectioners sugar, butter and milk.
Roll in coconut.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat the chicken broth in pan.
Combine cornstarch and cold water and stir until smooth.
Stir into hot chicken broth and cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Beat egg with whisk until frothy.
Gently stir into simmering broth and turn off heat immediately.
Egg should float like a cloud to surface. Serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: mango brown betty
directions: Melt margarine and add bread crumbs.
Sprinkle a layer of buttered crumbs in greased baking dish.
Add a layer of sliced mango.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and bread crumbs.
Add another layer of mangos, sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Pour orange juice over mixture and bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Put potato chunks in a baking pan or dish and cover with soup mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: crumb-topper cherry pie
directions: Pour filling into one pie shell. While the other pie shell is still frozen, crumble it into small pieces and mix with sugar, cinnamon, and pecans. Sprinkle evenly over cherries. Preheat oven to 425°, place pie on preheated cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 45-50 minutes. Cool completely before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in 1-inch boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine the rest of the ingredients; mix well and pour over the carrots. Refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight and serve cold.

title: kraut salad or corn salad
directions: Heat and pour over kraut and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: spanish beans
directions: Saute onion and pepper with 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix green beans until hot.
Mix eggs into beans (like scrambling eggs). Cook until eggs are done.
Serve with hot dry pepper.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine peanut butter, brown sugar, egg and vanilla in a bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Roll dough into small balls about 3/4 inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Flatten slightly.
Press one chocolate piece in center of each cookie.
Bake for 20 minutes until light brown. Kisses can be stored in airtight container for days.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fill 4 one pound coffee cans 1/2 full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese
with
2/3 cup sugar.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Add
vanilla
and
real lemon juice.
Pour into crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Add sour cream with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pour sour cream over pie and bake 10 minutes in
350° oven.
Let cool, then chill.
Add topping after pie is
well
chilled.
Use
your
favorite
pie filling (cherry, blueberry or strawberry).

title: microwave chicken sanchos
directions: Cook chicken in microwave for 5 to 7 minutes until done.
Cool slightly, cut meat in small pieces.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 of the jar of salsa and the tomatoes.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix the milk and 2 cups sugar in a saucepan; cook for 15 minutes.
Melt remaining sugar in an iron skillet over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add to the milk mixture.
Add the pecans and vanilla; beat until thick.
Pour onto well-buttered pan and cool. Cut into squares.

title: sausage fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions; drain. Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat. Add mushrooms and garlic; cook and stir until mushrooms are soft. Remove from skillet; set aside.
In same skillet, heat sausage over medium heat until lightly browned.
Drain any excess drippings.
Return mushroom mixture to skillet.
In small bowl, combine eggs and cream.
Add to skillet mixture; continue heating just until cream mixture is hot.
Do not boil. Add fettuccine; toss to combine. Mix in cheese and parsley. Serve immediately.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Beat until thick.
Fold in nondairy topping.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer bottom with whole graham crackers.
Pour pudding mix over crackers and add another layer of crackers on top of pudding.
Top with icing.

title: english trifle
directions: Mix jello with milk and vanilla.
Break angel food cake in pieces and place into bottom of deep Pyrex dish.
Use 1 layer of cake.
Pour layer of pudding.
Then layer with peaches, cherries and slivered almonds.
Keep layering until dish is full.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Then place layer of fruit and slivers of almonds on top.
Chill well before serving.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and broccoli.
Add soups, rice and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and heat approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine the seasonings with the oil and whisk vigorously. Toss the remaining ingredients and top with the dressing just prior to serving.

title: apple or peach crumb pie
directions: Peel, slice and arrange apples or peaches in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
If peaches are used, sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon; cut into butter.
Sprinkle over fruit and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together; cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Stand 5 minutes.
Knead 30 seconds.
Cool.

title: almighty bars
directions: Mix all crust ingredients together until crumbly.
Put 1/2 of crust mixture in an 11 x 14-inch greased pan.
Mix the apples, flour and cinnamon together and spread evenly over crust.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 of crust mixture over apples.
Beat egg whites until frothy and brush on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Drizzle with a powdered sugar glaze, if desired.

title: crisp oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine potato flakes, seasoned salt, paprika, garlic powder and pepper.
Add margarine; mix well.
In medium bowl, beat water with egg.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture; coat all sides with potato flake mixture. Place chicken skin side up in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 55 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: cream cheese snackin dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve with a variety of crackers.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with corn syrup.
Gradually add evaporated milk and egg to pudding mixture, stirring to blend.
Then stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until firm. Cool at least 3 hours.

title: sugar and cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix as cake.
Fill small muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350°. Cool.
Roll in melted butter, then roll in sugar and cinnamon.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushroom pieces in butter.
Cook broccoli as directed on package (don't overcook) and drain well. Add mushroom soup to sauteed ingredients.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Combine all in a chafing dish and serve.
Serves 12.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, orange juice and lemonade as directed on package and cans.
Add sugar to taste, about 2 cups.
Add lemon-lime soda if you want a little fizz at serving time.

title: grit bread
directions: Cook grits in 4 c. water until thick.
Add margarine, grated cheese and garlic cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add 3 beaten eggs. Stir until smooth.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2 qt. greased casserole dish and top with more shredded cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until set in the middle.

title: cornmeal waffles
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
In separate bowl beat together buttermilk, egg yolk and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients until all is moistened.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Bake in waffle iron as usual.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Have the ingredients in separate piles for assembling the enchiladas.
Heat 1 can cream of chicken soup and 3/4 can chicken broth (reserved from cooking the chicken).
Soften tortillas in cooled soup.
Place in equal amount of each ingredient on softened tortilla and roll.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with sour cream and a little of the leftover broth.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Should be enough for 5 large or 10 small enchiladas.

title: butter "gooey" cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. In mixer bowl, combine cake mix, eggs and butter.
Beat until well blended.
Batter will be thick.
Pour into pan.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain canned tuna.
Layer noodles, then tuna, cream of mushroom soup and chunks of Velveeta cheese. Layer these 4 ingredients again and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or 10 minutes in the microwave oven and brown under broiler.

title: chili
directions: Clean and dice onion; combine it with hamburger.
Cook in a large skillet until done, stirring often to insure that hamburger is broken up.
Drain off grease and combine in a large pot with tomato juice and beans.
Add 1/2 stick butter, diced green pepper and hot sauce.
Cook slowly about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
The amounts of hot sauce and green pepper can be adjusted to your individual taste.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream margarine with sugar and flour.
Add vanilla, salt and eggs.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: becky's best chicken
directions: Spray a casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Place chicken in dish.
Try not to overlap.
Drizzle with 1/3 cup Lea & Perrins white wine Worcestershire sauce.
Add garlic, oregano, paprika and lemon and herb seasoning.
Cover with aluminum foil and place in 350°
oven.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes and turn chicken over. Marinate again with white wine Worcestershire sauce. Bake for another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine catsup or chili sauce, vinegar, paprika and garlic powder.
Cover; chill for several hours.

title: gramma's biscuits
directions: Measure and sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in the shortening; stir in the buttermilk.
When thoroughly mixed, turn onto a floured board.
Knead and fold dough about 8 times, but keep the dough soft.
Roll to about 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured cutter or a glass.
Place on a baking pan and brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: savory swiss chard
directions: Brown bacon in large pot (5-quart pot).
Add sliced onion and garlic cloves, chopped fine.
Brown onion, then add garlic.
Now add tomatoes.
Crush the tomatoes to small pieces.
Also add half of tomato liquid and dried parsley.
Cook 10 minutes, covered, then add cleaned wet Swiss chard.
Cook until tender.
Serve hot.

title: date nut muffins
directions: Soak dates in
3 cups hot water 10 minutes to plump.
Drain off water and refrigerate dates.
They must be cold before using. Cream together oleo and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt, water, baking soda, pecans and flour.
Mix as little as possible because gluten will develop and make muffins tough.
Fold in dates.
Spoon batter into muffin cups and bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine cinnamon, 3 tablespoons sugar and pecans; set aside. Combine cake mix with 1/2 cup sugar and oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Fold in sour cream (do not beat).
Pour 1/2 the batter into a 10-inch greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and glaze.
Pour remaining batter in before baking.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, salt and cocoa with whisk.
Add milk and cook until thick and bubbling in microwave.
Add egg yolks, remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover
and
put
into
refrigerator
overnight.
(This improves the flavor.) When ready to bake, make crust.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon into a large bowl.
Add the oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in carrots, walnuts, coconut and pineapple.
Bake 1 hour or until the edges have pulled away from the side of the pan and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into bowl; add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli.
Drain.
Crush the Ritz crackers.
Melt 1 stick butter or margarine and Velveeta cheese together and add to broccoli.
Melt 1/2 stick butter or margarine and mix with crumbs. Alternate broccoli and crumbs in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: french toast
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 baking pan, arrange the bread slices. In a bowl, combine eggs, orange juice, milk, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg. Whisk until well blended. Pour over bread slices. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: rumaki hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar and ginger in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut bacon slices into halves.
Wrap a pineapple chunk and a water chestnut in each bacon piece.
Secure with wooden pick. Place in marinade and refrigerate, covered, for 2 hours.
Drain.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers; put into crock or jars.
Mix solution and pour over.
Grape leaves on top of pickles in crock will help keep pickles crisp.

title: macedonia fruit cup
directions: Pour orange and lemon juice into a large serving bowl.
Add seedless grapes and cherries.
Wash, peel and slice other fruit. Add each fruit to the bowl immediately after cutting it to prevent discoloration.
Serve chilled.
Yields 10 servings.
Serving Size: 1/2 cup.
One fruit, 60 calories per serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon or chocolate bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter or margarine and 1 egg.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet and sour ginger sauce
directions: Stir together these spice combinations and store in resealable plastic bags to use anytime on all your favorite grilled foods like beef, chicken, fish and pork -- even tofu!

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift 2 cups of flour over fruit and nuts.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, vanilla, cinnamon and 1 cup of flour.
Mix well.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
When done, pack into tube pans or loaf pans using the bottom of a Coke bottle.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease two large baking sheets.
In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Stir with rubber spatula until well blended and yeast is dissolved.

title: quick orange salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and dry Jell-O.
Add mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
You may use strawberry Jell-O and small container of frozen strawberries, if desired.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Cook caramels and condensed milk over low heat until melted. Stir often.
Remove from heat.
Mix brownie mix per directions on box and add chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts.
Place approximately 2/3 of batter in a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water.
Let cool.

Mix filling and pineapple with gelatin and let it congeal in a 14 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish. Beat cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and nuts together until fluffy. Spread evenly on congealed jello. Garnish with nuts.
Keep refrigerated. Serves 12.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Stir ingredients together in order listed.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 325° about 60 minutes.

title: 24 hour wine-cheese omelette
directions: Butter two 3-quart baking pans (9 x 13-inch).
Spread bread over bottom; drizzle butter over bread.
Sprinkle with shredded cheeses (and salami).
Beat together eggs, milk, wine, scallions, mustard and pepper until foamy; pour over cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.

title: perfect blender popovers
directions: Place eggs and milk in container of electric blender; blend until bubbly.
Add flour and salt; blend until smooth.
Fill well-greased popover cups half full.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 9 to 10 popovers.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add the oil; mix well.
Mix the salt, baking powder, baking soda, cake flour and cocoa together.
Mix alternately to the above mixture with the milk.
Last, add the hot coffee or hot water; mix well. (This cake batter will look thin.)
Bake in two greased 9-inch cake pans or two wax paper lined pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix soup, milk and Cheddar cheese in saucepan and heat until cheese melts.
Stir in onion and corned beef.
Mix together with macaroni in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Top with crushed crackers, French fried onions or whatever suits your taste.)
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fiesta cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand until well blended. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13 pan (Pam greased). Blend cream cheese, margarine, confectioners sugar and coconut flavoring. When cake is cool spread over cake.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and peanut butter. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: amish friendship bread(herman bread)
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in 2 large pans and 1 small pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: candied walnuts
directions: Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar and sour cream in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir until it boils.
Continue to boil until mixture is soft ball stage (240°; soft ball, dropped into cold water, is formed).
Stir in salt and vanilla.
Pour hot candy mixture over walnuts in a mixing bowl.
Mix until walnuts are evenly coated.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
Separate walnuts. Cool and when dry, store in airtight container.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed.
Whip together eggs, milk and half and half.
Pour over layered ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix first 5
ingredients
together
until
creamy.
Add coconut and pineapple.
Pour
into	unbaked pie shell. Cook 15 minutes at 425° and reduce	heat
to 350° and bake until firm, about 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions. Add broccoli for last 5 minutes of cooking time; drain. In skillet, mix soup, milk, cheese, chicken, onion powder, fettuccine and broccoli. Cook until heated through, stirring often.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salad dressing, salt and mustard together. Pour over cabbage, carrots and diced celery.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear cake into chunks and place into a large glass bowl. Combine dry gelatin with strawberries and mix well.
Pour over cake.
Pour prepared pudding on top of strawberry mixture.
Add Cool Whip topping on top.

title: aunt jo's pistachio pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Bundt pan with vegetable spray. Sprinkle with flour.
In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, 2 boxes of instant pudding, water, oil, eggs and milk.
Mix with blender 3 minutes.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until center springs back when touched.
Place on cooling rack.
Let cool 30 minutes.

title: christmas tree cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, stiffly beaten egg whites and water. Mix salt, baking powder and flour together; blend into creamed mixture.
Roll out on floured board; cut into desired shapes. Bake at 350° on lightly greased cookie sheet until edges are lightly browned.
Decorate with colored icing or colored sugar. Makes 6 dozen.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Add the marshmallows, pecans, raisins and chopped cherries to the melted milk chocolate.
Mix well and pour into a greased pizza pan. When still warm, add the cherry halves as garnish on top. Drizzle the white chocolate over.
Drizzle over top of all.
When set place on cake board.

title: warm honey dijon chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, honey, mustard and tarragon.
Reserve 1/2 cup. Pour remaining mixture over chicken in shallow baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate 20 minutes or overnight to marinate.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Put in crock-pot and cook slow all day.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Grate cheese.
Cream margarine and cheese.
Set aside.
Mix flour, paprika, dry mustard and red pepper.
Add cheese and margarine.
Mix well.
Use a cookie maker and make the desired type of wafer.
Bake on greased cookie sheet until light golden brown at 300°.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt, then add eggs, Karo syrup, butter and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then at 300° until done.

title: lamb pilaf
directions: Wash and chop the pepper finely.
Season the corn flour and toss the lamb cubes in it.
Heat the oil and brown the meat on all sides.
Remove and keep warm.
In the same saucepan, fry the onions and the chopped pepper; add the tomatoes, the chicken cube, raisins, lemon juice and 2 cups boiling water.
We stir in the rice; put everything in an ovenproof casserole.
Season and place the meat on top of the rice mixture; cover and bake at 300° or 160°C oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until rice has absorbed all the liquid.
Serves 4.

title: three bean bake
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Reserve enough drippings to saute onion and green pepper.
Crumble bacon and save.
Combine onion mixture, bacon and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bake in 2 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
If fat gram conscious, use vegetarian baked beans and omit bacon.
Saute in Pam.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: soybean patties
directions: Mix well and add if needed 1/4 cup flour.
Drop by large spoonful into sprayed frying pan or bake as a loaf in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: toot's banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and well beaten eggs.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Add 1 cup flour.
Add bananas and rest of flour.
Bake for 1 hour or more at 350°.

title: fish miso yaki
directions: Fillet fish or cut into pieces.
Combine
all
ingredients, except green onions.
Marinate fish in sauce for about 2 hours. Put
oil in skillet; fry fish, skin
side
first,
at medium-low heat.
Turn fish, lower heat and
cover
pan.
Just before taking out, sprinkle green onions on top.	Can
be used for beef and pork, also.

title: broccoli soup 2
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add flour.
Stir vigorously until blended.
Heat milk.
Add broccoli to broth mixture, then add milk.
Heat together 5 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip delight
directions: Pour a little milk in a bowl.
In a round Pyrex bowl (deep), make first layer of cookies.
First, dip cookies in milk (couple of seconds) and make first layer.
Open Cool Whip and spread on a layer over cookies.
Continue doing this until you run out of cookies.
Try to leave one cookie to break up on top for decoration.
Chill overnight.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Break chocolate bar in half and grate.
Beat cake mix, eggs, water, oil and pudding mix at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and 1/2 grated chocolate bar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Mix remaining grated chocolate with confectioners sugar and sprinkle over cake while warm.
Cake should be baked in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan.

title: fruit cake cookies(may prepare ahead.)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add milk, flour, soda, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and whiskey.
Mix well.
Flour fruit with 1/2 cup reserved flour. Pour batter over fruit and mix.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 35 minutes.

title: lillian's passover farfel nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Toast farfel lightly on cookie sheet in oven.
(A few minutes is all that is necessary.) Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Mix melted chocolate, farfel, nuts and raisins in bowl.
Drop mixture from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until hard.
May be stored in cookie tin.
Delicious!

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add small amount of egg at a time.
Cook 1 minute.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked crust.
Top with meringue, if desired.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Heat chili sauce and jelly until jelly dissolves.
Add cocktail wieners.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread bread with dressing.
Layer 6 slices of bread with 1 slice cheese, sauerkraut, corned beef and 1 slice cheese.
Serve cold or brush sandwich with butter and grill for hot sandwich. Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Set out 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prepare Basic Tomato Meat Sauce.

title: broccoli rice soup
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Brown bacon in skillet; drain on paper towel.
Brown onion in same skillet.
Cook broccoli in saucepan until tender; do not drain.
Put onion and 2 tablespoons of drippings in pan with broccoli.
Add salt, pepper and rice.
Warm slowly while adding milk.
Crumble bacon on top. Serves 4.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into a quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: crunchy tuna and potato chip casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Flake the tuna and place in casserole.
Add onion and pepper.
Gently stir ingredients together.
Pour condensed mushroom soup over ingredients in casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chip pieces and grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in preheated oven.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower with cheese and chili sauce
directions: Cook cauliflower in a small amount of boiling salted water in a large saucepan for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender; drain.
Cook onion, green or red pepper in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes or until tender in a covered saucepan.
Stir together milk and flour until smooth and stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, then continue to cook for 1 minute more. Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in green chili peppers and hot pepper sauce; heat through.
Place cauliflower on a serving plate and pour some of the cheese sauce over the top.
Pass the remaining sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; chop and set aside.
Remove seeds and parboil whole peppers a few at a time, for about 5 minutes. Invert on paper towel to drain.

title: pralines
directions: Lightly coat wax paper with vegetable cooking spray; set aside. Combine sugars, butter, milk and pecans in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil, uncovered, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes or until a candy thermometer reaches 220°.
(You may need to lower heat if using a thinner saucepan and rely on the candy thermometer.) Remove from heat and beat mixture with a wooden spoon 4 to 6 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Cook raisins in enough water so that there will be 1 cup liquid left.
To this liquid, add the shortening.
Sift dry ingredients, except for soda, and to this add raisins, then liquid.
Add well-beaten egg, then nuts.
Lastly add soda to small amount of water and add to batter.
Bake in greased and floured shallow pan at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
While still warm, cover with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients together, stirring, until mixture comes to a boil and is slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice and sprinkle with almonds or Macadamia nuts.
Serves 8.

title: special sheet cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box in 12 x 18-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.
Mix pudding and milk until slightly thick; add softened cream cheese.
Spread on cooled cake.
Sprinkle with drained crushed pineapple.
Layer thick layer Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in pan with 1/2 cup water.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Drain liquid into frying pan with flour and dissolve.
Add 2 cups water, salt and pepper and heat until it slightly thickens.
Pour back into pan with roast.
Cut potatoes into wedges and put into gravy.
Cover with foil.
Return to oven and bake to desired tenderness.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cook until tender. Drain well and mash. Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings.
Remove from heat and add egg, salt, pepper and onion mixture.
Spoon half of the mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese. Spoon remaining eggplant over the cheese and top evenly with picante sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with romaine lettuce and croutons.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Bake in a glass dish at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together the next 3 ingredients (cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip).
Spread this mixture over crust and refrigerate.
Whip the last 3 ingredients together; spread over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate until pudding sets.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with pecans and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot sweet-sour mustard
directions: Mix ingredients in top of double boiler.
Stir constantly for about 10 minutes.
Pour in sterile jars. Refrigerate after opening jars.
Great with ham.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Prepare dough according to package directions.
Roll out dough (not too thin) and brush with eggs.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Lay on pepperoni or salami, enough to cover dough.
Sprinkle cheese on top of pepperoni.
Roll dough up, jelly roll style, tucking the ends in while rolling.
Glaze with eggs and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until tops are brown.
Cool before cutting, about 5 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Layer in greased pan.
Combine oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon; cut in butter.
Sprinkle oatmeal mixture over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with Cheddar cheese, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Melt the chocolate and margarine together; cool slightly. Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar; mix well.
Add chocolate mixture. Add the flour, salt and vanilla.
Drop onto medium hot waffle iron.
Bake for about 1 1/2 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken; pull meat off bones.
Line bottom of dish with chicken, top with sliced, boiled eggs, salt and pepper.
Combine soup and broth and pour over chicken and eggs.
Combine milk, oleo and flour, mix well and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.	Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix together flour and nuts. Add to brown sugar mixture.
Spread in a 9 inch x 13 inch greased pan.
Bake in 350 oven for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm. Remove from pan when cool.	Yield:	3 dozen bars.

title: beefy italian minestrone
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine beef stew, tomatoes, green beans and basil. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Stir in pasta. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.

title: adobo (manok) chicken
directions: Marinate chicken with salt, pepper and onions about 1/2 hour. Put all ingredients in pan and cook over medium heat until chicken is tender and liquid has cooked down to about half.
Serve with fluffy rice.

title: five-minute soup
directions: Heat the broth.
Add the vegetables and meat.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yield: about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in small amounts for boiling.
Drain thoroughly. Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and paprika.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Place remaining cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles and cheese on top is melted, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bamboo chicken
directions: Cook shrimp, fish sauce, sugar and salt on high for 5 minutes. Add peas, chicken, sherry and soy sauce.
Stir to combine all ingredients well.
Bring to a boil.
Add bamboo shoots and mushrooms.
Stir and heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: phyllis' cheese balls with olives
directions: Blend and knead with hands.
Make small balls around small stuffed olives.
Freeze.
Bake frozen in 350° oven 15 minutes in an ungreased pan.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle into pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients to eggs.
Pour into pie shell over cheese and sausage.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: one dish pasta and vegetables
directions: In large saucepan, prepare macaroni according to package. Add carrots and broccoli for last 5 minutes of cooking time. Drain. In same pan, mix soup, milk and mustard into the macaroni mix. Heat throughout over medium heat, stirring often. Makes 5 servings.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Sift flour and salt and add to mixture.
Stir in pecans and chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake about 9 to 10 minutes in a 400°
oven until set but not brown.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again.

title: easy crock-pot roast
directions: Place
vegetables
in
bottom
of crock-pot. Add roast. Pour tomato
juice over roast.
Sprinkle au jus mix and onion over roast. Cover.
Cook on high for 2 hours.
Turn to low and cook 2 to 3 hours more.

title: stir-fry
directions: Mix soy sauce and dressing and place in medium size bowl. Marinate chicken in mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet in salad oil.
Remove chicken to bowl. In drippings, cook onions, green peppers, cut into strips.
Add peach liquid from can to skillet, stir in vinegar, soy sauce, brown sugar, salt and pepper and 1/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat to low.
Add chicken.
Simmer 30 minutes.
In cup, mix cornstarch and 4 tablespoons water into simmering chicken liquid. Add peaches and tomatoes and heat.
Serve over rice.

title: southern yams and pineapple
directions: Cook yams, peel and slice in half.
Combine pineapple juice, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Mix well. Cook until sauce boils and thickens, stirring. Stir in vinegar.
Add yams and pineapple slices.
Cover and simmer.
Fry onions, celery and green pepper for 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine with yams and pineapple. Serve immediately. Very good the breaded pork chops.

title: spicy stuffed peppers
directions: Cook peppers in boiling, salted water for 3 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine ground beef, onion, rice and seasoning.
Spoon into peppers.
Place in a greased baking dish. Top with picante sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Yields 4 servings.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sherbet, mixing well.
Add drained oranges and pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream.
Congeals quickly.
Chill.

title: colonial holiday ring
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add to butter and sugar.
Beat together.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add orange rind, dates and pecans.
Pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done before removing from pan.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in cake all the way to the bottom with ice pick.
Glaze with orange juice and powdered sugar, mixed to thin consistency.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into large bowl.
Add onion, egg and milk.
Stir until just mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, corn syrup and vanilla in saucepan. Bring to boil.
Beat eggs and pour syrup mixture in slowly.
Put pecans in bottom of pie shell and pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: breaded chicken
directions: Wash chicken and let drain, then roll in flour.
Take eggs and fold in milk then dip floured chicken into it.
Combine both cups of bread crumbs, add pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Then take chicken and roll into bread crumbs.
In a large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken on both sides.
Arrange chicken in large baking pan with rack.
Add 1 cup of water and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: nola's corn relish
directions: Cook one hour and can.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Warm milk. Add Grape-Nuts and let stand for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs and add to milk mixture.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with nutmeg as you wish.
Place casserole in a pan of warm water and bake 1 hour at 325° or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown ground chuck with salt, pepper and garlic.
Drain.
Add large Mozzarella cheese.
Stir until mixed well.
Cook noodles about half the time the box says.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water. Stuff with meat and cheese mixture.
Place in 9 x 12-inch pan or baking dish.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over stuffed noodles.
(Joanne Engelman's Spaghetti Sauce.)
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Eat!

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Mix broccoli, onion, cottage cheese, eggs, margarine and hot sauce.
Stir in muffin mix.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Freezes well.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix together and let sit overnight in the refrigerator and serve.
Delicious!

title: frozen punch
directions: Cook water and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Cool.

title: pineapple-raisin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Blend in pineapple juice concentrate, butter and vanilla.
Add flour, oats, baking soda, salt and spices; mix well.
Stir in pineapple, pecans and raisins.
Spread batter into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until firm.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 16 bars.

title: beef, cabbage and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Layer cabbage and sliced potatoes in baking dish; also layer beef.
Cover with tomato sauce and mix garlic with vinegar, salt and pepper.
Spread over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Combine shortening, spices, salt, brown sugar, molasses and eggs and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour and soda.
Add flour and sour milk to first mixture.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut with cutter.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange frosted
directions: Combine orange juice and water; mix well.
Add ice cream; beat 1 minute with electric mixer.
Serve in tall glasses.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: native american pudding
directions: Heat milk in saucepan.
Add molasses and cornmeal to the milk. Stir until it is all mixed together.
Now boil.
Remove the pan from the heat.
Add the butter, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Stir in the beaten eggs.

title: meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, catsup, water and dry soup mix.
Put into loaf pan and cover with bacon.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat sugar, flour, oleo and eggs well.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans, coconut and vanilla; pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until firm.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and cherry pie filling into baking pan, 8 x 13-inches. Sprinkle cake mix over top. Then sprinkle chopped pecans over it and top with sliced pieces of margarine. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: seafood alfredo a la loftus
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package directions; drain.
Cook broccoli until fork-tender, but crunchy; drain.
Prepare Alfredo sauce according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients. Let sit for 5 minutes.
Parmesan cheese may be grated over top.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Combine ingredients in baking dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until it falls off bone (about 30 minutes). Remove all chicken from bones.
Cut into pieces.
Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs and melted butter into casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat milk to scalding in double boiler.
Add bread crumbs and cook until a thin, smooth paste is formed.
Add salt, then salmon which has been mashed to a pulp after all bones and undesirable portions have been removed, then add cream.
Heat to scalding and pour over beaten eggs.
Season with lemon juice and pepper and pour into buttered loaf pan.
Set in another pan containing hot water and bake in a slow oven (325° to 350°) for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Let stand a few minutes.
Unmold and serve on a hot platter and serve with Hollandaise Sauce.

title: chicken aluette
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pound chicken breast between wax paper to flatten slightly.
Cut sheets of puff pastry if large and roll out to hold each piece of chicken.
Spread cheese spread on chicken and put on puff pastry.
Fold over and seal edges.
It will look like pocket pastry.
Paint with egg wash and put in oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
I have done it without the egg wash and it works.

title: chewy delight
directions: Stir well and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
This is a real quick dessert.

title: five minute fudge(makes about 2 pounds)
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons butter, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Start timing when mixture starts to "bubble" around edges of pan.)

title: quick fudge candy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and milk.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour out to cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and cream again.
Add mashed bananas and extract.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder; add to mixture, then add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Add mixture and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Then add the frozen concentrated lemon juice. Stir until firm.
Put in graham cracker crusts.
Chill 2 hours and serve.

title: chicken angelo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in eggs; coat with bread crumbs.
Saute chicken in olive oil until brown.
Transfer to a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the mushrooms; cover with cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining mushrooms and pour chicken broth over all.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: party pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops until brown.
Place in shallow baking dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Slice green pepper and onion.
Place over pork chops.
Mix milk and soup, pour over pork chops.
Bake in oven at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add one egg at a time. Beat well each time.
Make paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to mixture.
Sift flour and salt.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately, starting and ending with flour.
Combine soda and vinegar and add to batter.
Beat well.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch square pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine cranberries, 3/4 cup sugar, orange juice and water in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook 10 minutes or until cranberries are soft.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter
and 1/2 cup sugar at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in sour cream, orange rind and nutmeg.
Spoon batter into pan.
Top with cranberry mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 1 cake.

title: cheese noodle snack
directions: Put butterscotch in top of double boiler.
Melt and stir in noodles and nuts.
Put on oil paper to cool in small spoonfuls.

title: banana split dessert
directions: For Crust:
Metl
1 stick oleo.
Mix with graham crackers. Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Then dip in chocolate.
Melt 2 large Hershey bars with 1/2 block paraffin.
Keep hot while dipping.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cook pineapple, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool completely before putting on cake.
I double this recipe because I like the cake to be gooey.

title: chuck roast
directions: Heat soup and water.
Put all ingredients in roasting bag and bake at 350° for about 3 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add nuts, syrup, flavoring and margarine, beating lightly.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Pecans will float to top, forming a nice brown crust.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup together.
Microwave on High power for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes or until light brown.
Add vanilla, butter and microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes or until peanuts are light brown and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet. Shake to spread.
Cool 1 hour.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add dry Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and stir until combined. Fold in Cool Whip and spoon in dish you wish to serve it in. Sprinkle, if you desire, with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare your crust; do not bake.
Peel and slice the apples thin.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with as much cinnamon as you prefer in apple pie, also adding 2 tablespoons flour and sprinkle over the apples.
Take 1 cube frozen butter and cut or grate into 1 cup flour plus 1/2 cup sugar.
Use a pastry cutter or fork to blend the three together.
Sprinkle this over the apples and place the pie in a large brown bag from the grocery store.
Staple the bag shut to avoid any steam escaping.
Place this on a cookie sheet and bake. Do not open the oven door for any reason as the bag will catch on fire.
Bake 1/2 hour at 400°, then 1 hour at 350°.
Warm the pie to serve.
Do not try to make more than 1 pie at a time in one oven.

title: hazelnut cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add ground hazelnuts, salt and flour. Roll between waxed paper about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix as you would any other cake.
Bake at 350° until it springs back when touched, about 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Let sausage and cheese come to room temperature.
Mix sausage, bisquick and milk.
Form into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar.
Combine pecans, eggs and dates.
Mix well together.
Cook 10 minutes over low heat in skillet, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and Rice Krispies. Cool until able to handle.
Roll in balls, then in coconut.
Will freeze well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add carrots, oil, pineapple, vanilla and eggs.
Mix, add nuts and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed flounder(serves 1)
directions: Combine Melba toast, spices and water.
Place flounder in baking dish and top with Melba toast mixture.
Roll ends and hold with toothpicks.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.

title: no flour oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix everything together.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. If desired, flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing.

title: tangy chicken wings
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients, except chicken wings; boil for 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken wings in a baking pan.
Bake for 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 450°.

title: mom's raisin sauce("great with ham")
directions: Cook raisins, ham and pineapple in 4 cups water for 20 minutes.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and 1 tablespoon of water and add to raisin mixture. Stir until thickened.
Serve over ham.

title: bierocks(german hamburger)
directions: Steam cabbage and onion until cabbage wilts and onion is transparent.
Brown beef and drain.
Combine onion, cabbage and beef; let cool.
Meanwhile mash together 2 rolls and roll into circle.
Put 4 tablespoons meat mixture on circle; draw up sides. Turn pinched side down.
Place on greased cookie sheet, don't crowd.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes. Yield:
12 rolls.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg and 1/3 cup sugar for center.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt, then add water, vinegar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Drop one heaping teaspoon in middle of chocolate batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Spray pan or dish with Pam.
Mix soup and milk.
Place layer of potatoes, layer of onion, layer of soup mixture and a layer of cheese.
Continue layering in this fashion.
On top layer of onions, put a small amount of margarine on casserole.
End casserole with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are soft.
May also be microwaved.

title: bread-n-squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes in oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir and cook until thickened and clear 1/2 box crushed strawberries, powdered sugar and cornstarch.
Cool.
Slice other 1/2 box of strawberries.
Stir in.
Pour into baked pie shell. Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mustard-apricot pork chops
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat, cook and stir preserves and mustard until preserves have melted.
Set aside.
Place pork chops on lightly greased broiler pan.
Broil 4-inches from the heat for 5 minutes.
Brush with half of the glaze; turn chops. Broil 5 minutes longer.
Brush with the rest of the glaze.
Broil 2 to 4 minutes longer or until meat juice runs clear.
Top with the diced onions and serve over cooked rice or alone.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: In small bowl, mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
In large bowl beat eggs, margarine, milk and vanilla.
Gradually beat in sugar mixture; pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool before cutting.
Filling is set, but somewhat soft in center.

title: fried chicken
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Coat chicken with mixture by shaking bag.
Place pieces on wire rack and let dry about 15 minutes before frying.
In 12-inch frying pan, over medium-high heat, brown chicken on all sides in hot oil, turning frequently.
Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and cook until tender.
Remove cover for last few minutes to crisp chicken.

title: salsa
directions: Chop all fine and put in a large container. Cook about 30 to 35 minutes. Put in hot jars and seal. Makes about 5 pints.

title: lemon butter
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and continue beating.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Mix well on low speed.
Melt butter in double boiler and add to mixture.
Stir well and cook, stirring frequently until thick.
Serve in tart shells, between cake layers or spread on toast, biscuits, muffins or bread.
Good on ice cream, Boston cream pie or all alone.
Also called lemon curd.

title: bethel spoon bread
directions: Cream the margarine with a spoon. Add slightly beaten eggs, sour cream and both cans of corn.
Mix well. Add muffin mix.
Pour in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix together and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put remaining onion rings on top the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: broccoli with black olives
directions: Cook broccoli in a small amount of water for 10 minutes (or in a microwave according to directions); drain.
Saute garlic in olive oil until lightly browned.
Add broccoli and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add olives and heat 2 more minutes.
Serve immediately and sprinkle with cheese.
Add salt and pepper at the table. Serves 4 (90 calories per serving).

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients and put into plastic container.
Add 2 heaping teaspoons into 1 cup boiling water.
Refrigerate dry mixture.

title: sweet and savory beans
directions: Cook onion until tender in hot margarine in a 10-inch skillet. Add beans, syrup and mustard.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed.
Slowly add condensed milk and beat.
Slowly add pink lemonade and beat.
Add food coloring and beat.
Pour in cooled pie shells and chill several hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bob's potato casserole
