directions: Mix defrosted hash browns together with other ingredients (except corn flakes and last 1/2 cup melted butter).
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with corn flakes.
Dribble butter over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, toss together peppers, onions, squash, zucchini, garlic, olive oil and oregano.
Spread the vegetables on a baking sheet or metal roasting pan and roast for 20 minutes, or until tender, stirring several times.

title: apple chiffon cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: indian pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Butter a shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish or large casserole.
In heavy saucepan, heat milk over medium heat.
Slowly sprinkle in the cornmeal, whisking as you do so. Continue to stir with a wooden spoon for 10 minutes, until thickened.
Lower heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Pour carefully into baking dish.
Bake for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Serve warm.
Top with vanilla ice cream.

title: tomato soup
directions: Bring to boil
tomatoes, sliced but not peeled, onions, parsley, celery and 2
quarts
water.
Boil until tender.
Run through
sieve.
Combine
flour,
sugar,
paprika,
salt
and butter.
Add 1 pint water
and cook until thick.
Add to soup. Pour in jars.
Cold pack about
1/2 hour.
I also add 14 whole cloves and 2 or 3 bay leaves.
Makes about 14 quarts.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease casserole dish.	Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole
dish.
Place
6 to 8 pieces of chicken on top of rice
mixture.
Sprinkle
chicken
with
1	package of Lipton onion soup	mix.
Seal
with
foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek!!!! Serves 6.

title: apple butter
directions: In a large roasting pan, combine applesauce and the other ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or longer, until thick and dark.
Makes 3 pints.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except beef.
Add beef; mix well.
Pat mixture into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in
a 325° oven for about 1 hour.

title: cheddar cheese sticks
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter.
Add cheese and mix well.
Add enough water to hold ingredients together.
Roll out on floured board to 14 x 8-inch rectangle.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Fold corners into center.
Roll out again and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Fold in corners again.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for 30 minutes.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness and cut into strips.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine butter, salt and water.
Heat to boiling. Sift flour and measure.
Add to boiling mixture.
Beat vigorously until mix leaves side of pan and does not cling.
Remove from fire.
Cool slightly.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly after each egg.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto sheets, well oiled. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° for 10 minutes more, or until dry.
Remove and cool.
Makes 6 servings.

title: holiday ham ball
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart in lightly greased pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp and hot sauce
directions: Use 2 sticks for every pound of shrimp.
Mix butter and hot sauce together and cook shrimp until they turn red.
Slice French bread in thick slices to dip in butter sauce.

title: cashew fudge
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan. In a saucepan, melt butter and add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat for about 2 minutes, stirring until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Gradually add confectioners sugar until the mixture is of fudge consistency. Add nuts. Pour and spread into prepared pan. Let cool.
Makes about 36 pieces.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool crust. Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry Ranch dressing and spread over rolls.
Top with any vegetable.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together. Bake in 9x5x2 loaf pan at 350° for 2 hrs.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel and cut in slices, apples.
Put in bottom of crust.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; pour over apples.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly.
Pour on top of pie mixture. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles using package directions, drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, onion, and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat and add grated cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add this to noodle mixture.
Pour into a 2 qt. casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 425 for 20 minutes.

title: hunter stew
directions: Wash and cut squirrel in pieces as you would to fry.
Place in large pan with 3 or 4 gallons of water.
Put squirrel, bacon, pepper, salt and beans.
Let cook until squirrel is tender.
Add potatoes and 1 stick of butter.
Cut the ears of corn in half and add them.
Let all cook together but not to pieces.
Serve with hot corn bread sticks.

title: crispy kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut well.
Meanwhile, chop onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix the dressing from vinegar, oil and sugar.
Blend all ingredients together and marinate for an hour or longer.
Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 6 servings.

title: teddy bear bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk mixture and 3 cups unsifted flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough additional flour (3 1/2 to 4 cups) to make a stiff dough.

title: coke salad
directions: Boil the sugar and water.
Add the jello; stir until dissolved.
Add the cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple, Coke and chopped nuts.
Mix together.
Refrigerate, covered, for at least 3 hours.

title: fannie farmer's million dollar fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips and marshmallow cream in a large bowl and set aside.

title: stir-fry pork
directions: Heat margarine in a large heavy skillet.
Add onion and stir-fry for 3 minutes, until partially cooked.
Add apples and stir-fry over high heat 3 more minutes.
Add juice or water. Cover skillet; simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove lid; stir in pork and sprinkle with seasonings.
Stir in sour cream and stir-fry to heat thoroughly.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt into a large bowl.
Add the fruit, carrots and nuts; stir to combine.
In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs with the oil and vanilla.
Pour this mixture into the bowl with dry ingredients and blend well.
Spoon the batter into lightly greased muffin tins.
Fill each cup to the brim.

Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center of a muffin is withdrawn clean. Cool muffins in the pan for 10 minutes, then turn out and finish cooling on a rack.
These muffins need 24 hours to develop their full flavor.
They freeze well.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, carrots, onions and hamburger in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix tomato soup and mushroom soup and garden peas with liquid; pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend all ingredients except food coloring and pie shell.
Add enough food coloring to desired shade.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: brownies macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir in the middle of cooking to mix cheese.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat egg. Add corn, followed by other ingredients, with milk last. Bake in buttered casserole at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine squash, onions, red peppers and green peppers in large bowl.
Add salt; mix well.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse.
Combine sugar, celery seed, mustard seed, turmeric and vinegar in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetable mixture; mix well. Bring to a boil.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Yield:
60 servings.

title: all in one supper
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides
in skillet over moderate heat.
Combine tomatoes, chopped onion, salt, sugar, rice, and celery together.
Pour tomato mixture over pork chops, cover, and turn to low heat. Cook until rice and pork chops are done.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients until dissolved.
Add pie filling; let set.

title: peanut butter oatmeal patties
directions: Beat eggs well and add seasonings and onion.
Beat together milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add oatmeal and mix well. If mixture is too wet to form into patties, add a little more oatmeal; if too dry, add a small amount of milk.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Brown on both sides.
Put into a casserole dish.
Mix soup with water until well blended and pour over patties.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
May substitute tomato or mushroom soup if you prefer.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake in a buttered oven dish for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: tender roast beef
directions: In Dutch oven or large pot, fry bacon.
Remove bacon.
Brown beef in bacon fat on all sides.
Put 2 cups hot water in Dutch oven with bay leaf and onion; simmer 3 hours.
Take roast out and let it cool slightly.
Slice thin.

title: nutty chocolate sauce
directions: In a nonstick saucepan or skillet, melt butter and saute nuts until slightly toasted.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and stir until melted.	Serve warm over ice cream.
Sauce will harden. Store remaining sauce in refrigerator.
Reheat (melted) in a microwave for future use.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: senate restaurant bean soup
directions: Take beans and wash and run through hot water until beans are white again.
Add beans to 4 quarts of boiling water.
Add smoked ham hocks and simmer approximately 3 hours in covered pot.
Remove ham hocks; chop meat and return to soup.
Saute onion in a little butter and when light brown, put in soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add salt when ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with cut up vegetables or potato chips.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Fold in extracts.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: krabbsallad(crab salad)
directions: Drain the crabmeat and remove any membranes.
Combine the crabmeat, celery, onion, lemon juice, dill, sour cream and pepper. Mix gently.
Arrange salad on a lettuce leaf.

title: chicken chalupa
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan and line with tortilla chips.
Cook, bone and chop chicken.
Spread on top of chips.
Mix together soups, sour cream, chicken broth, chilies and onion.
Spread mixture on chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly.
Garnish with tomato wedges and avocado slices.
Return to oven to warm garnish.
Let set a few minutes before cutting.

title: raisin oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, grated rind and vanilla. Stir dry ingredients together.
Add oatmeal, raisins and nuts. Drop by spoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put margarine, peanut butter and vanilla in a 3-quart Tupperware (no need to mix), covered, in microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Add confectioners sugar; stir.
Spread evenly in Modular Mates Rectangle 1.
Refrigerate to firm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine until melted.
Blend in flour, onions, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in broth and milk. Heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar in small saucepan and cook just until sugar dissolves. Cool, then store in refrigerator. Mix together the sliced cucumbers, salt and onion. Let stand about 2 hours. Drain and squeeze out all water; pack in plastic containers. Pour syrup over pickle mixture, leaving 1/2-inch top for expansion. Cover and freeze.

title: apple scallop
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Mix in fat with a fork until crumbly.
Set aside.
Peel and slice apples.
Put in a baking pan or dish.
Sprinkle apples with white sugar and water. Spread crumbly mixture on top.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) about 30 minutes, until lightly browned and apples are tender.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crust.
Add pie filling.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: thirza's white lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, soup, oregano and salt. Add milk and pepper; blend.
Butter 12 x 8-inch casserole.
Layer noodles, chicken mix and cheese.
Bake about 40 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Melt caramels and cream in double boiler.
Cool slightly. Combine in bowl the flour, rolled oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and butter.
Press half of mixture into 12 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread caramel mixture on top.
Add rest of mixture and bake 20 minutes. Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Prepare pie crust per package instructions.
Mash enough strawberries to measure 1 cup.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water and strawberries gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: coated peanuts
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and water.
Pour raw peanuts into mixture.
Cook until all liquid is gone.
Must be completely dry and no shine.
(Stir with a wooden spoon.) Pour onto cookie sheet. Cook for 20 minutes at 300°.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Take out and pour onto cool cookie sheet.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture to
sugar mixture, small amount at a time.
Fold in fruit and
nuts.
Divide equally in 4 coffee tins.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.
Remove from cans.

title: summer garden salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Blend salad dressing, peel and juice of 1 lemon.

title: potato soup
directions: Put potatoes, onion, celery, butter, salt and pepper in pan with 1/2 pan water.
Bring to a boil then simmer till potatoes are done.
Add milk to fill up pan and add cheese, stir to melt.
Add instant potatoes till thick as you want them.

title: microwave ground beef gumbo
directions: Combine beef, onion and green pepper in 2-quart microproof casserole.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes on High, or until beef is no longer red, stirring once during cooking.
Break up beef with fork; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover. Cook on High for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking time.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 5 people.
Total cooking time: 9 to 11 minutes.

title: tasty chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon strips into thirds.
Wrap around chestnuts and hold with a toothpick.
Place on a pan, pour soy sauce over chestnuts. Broil approximately 5 minutes.

title: raspberry crepes
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly over crepes.
Sprinkle with half of almonds; roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Place seam side down on dish.
Drain raspberries, reserving 1/2 cup juice; set berries aside.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: Cook meat, waterless, in heavy Dutch oven or in electric skillet on low until very tender.
Remove meat to plate.
Scrape brown drippings loose.
Add water, bouillon or broth and sauerkraut.
Cover and continue cooking.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces and add to sauerkraut with brown sugar and onion.
Cook 1 hour.
If necessary, add additional water/bouillon or broth.
Last 25 minutes add noodles.
Stir occasionally until noodles are tender.
Can be made with Polish or any sausage.

title: ham glaze
directions: Combine sugar, juice and honey.
Remove ham 30 minutes before done baking; remove drippings.
Score top of ham in crisscross pattern.
Coat ham with glaze.
Bake in hot oven (400°).
Baste ham with rest of glaze, in 2 or 3 applications, every 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not baste ham with glaze from drippings as it dulls luster of glaze.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter, milk, Fluff and salt.
Cook and stir over low heat until blended.
Cook and stir 5 minutes at full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate.
Stir until chocolate is melted and blended well.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen squares.

title: elaine hurst's eggless, milkless cake
directions: Combine apples, raisins, water, brown sugar, white sugar and lard in a large saucepan and cook 5 minutes.
Cool completely. Sift the remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add apple-raisin mixture.
Blend well.
Add 1 cup walnuts or pecans.
Pour into greased and floured pan, 9 x 12-inch and bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until cake is done.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, salt, pepper, eggs and flour.
Stir until well mixed.
Spoon out ingredients into frypan with oil covering the bottom.
Turn when done.
Brown each side.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Combine ripe blackberries, water, sugar, and butter in large saucepan.
Bring blackberry mixture to boil.
Add dumplings a spoonful at a time into boiling mixture.
Cover lid, reduce heat slightly to prevent sticking, and cook covered for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ultra low fat chicken mozzarella
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken breasts in egg white, roll in corn flakes and place in large skillet sprayed with Pam buttery nonstick cooking spray.
Brown on both sides.
Spray a shallow baking dish with nonstick cooking spray and place chicken breasts in dish.
Mix water with spaghetti sauce and pour over chicken breasts.
Cover top with shredded fat free Mozzarella cheese and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Gram of fat per serving, 4; calories per serving, 313.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix potato soup, drained; mix veggies, milk and spices, and chicken.
In pie pan, add one pie crust; add meat mix.
Then top crust.
Cut a couple cuts.

title: chicken or turkey hot dish
directions: Combine stuffing mix and melted butter.
Press 1/2 into a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Combine chicken, soup, evaporated milk, vegetables, onion and pimento, mix well.
Spread in prepared dish. Top with remaining stuffing mix.
(You can put cheddar cheese on top.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fryer and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Place in large casserole dish; arrange fryer on top.
Cover tightly; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces before placing on rice.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl; blend well, then beat at medium speed around 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not underbake.

title: scramble
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: mozzarella and mushroom skillet pie
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 400°.

In a 10-inch skillet with oven-safe handle (or cover skillet handle with heavy-duty foil when baking in oven later), over medium-high heat, in hot olive or salad oil, cook onion and green pepper until onion is lightly browned. Stir in pizza sauce; remove skillet from heat.
In medium bowl, with wire whisk, beat milk, buttermilk baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour egg mixture into vegetable mixture in skillet.
Sprinkle with mushrooms, olives and half of the shredded Mozzarella. Bake 30 minutes. Remove skillet from oven.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and remaining Mozzarella cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together, then mix in other ingredients in order.
Punch holes in the pie crust with a fork and cook a little bit before putting the ingredients in.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: walking tacos
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread on beans.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients and then add dry mixture. Chill for 1 hour.
Roll cookies into balls and then in sugar and cinnamon.
Press with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together
rice,
mayonnaise, soup and curry powder. In buttered casserole	layer
broccoli,
chicken and rice mixture. Top with cheese.
Sprinkle	on bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Toss with butter, salt and pepper.
Mix dry mustard with a little hot water and add to milk.
Add egg and milk to noodles.
Add cheese, reserving some to sprinkle on top. Pour in a small buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in buttered, square Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for about one hour or until browned.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil until it begins to thicken.
Beat off in cold water. Pour in platter.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Add sour cream and most of the Cool Whip.
Spread between layers of bananas and vanilla wafers. Put some Cool Whip on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and onion until done, having at least 2 quarts of broth left.
Remove chicken from broth.
Allow to cool.
Add potatoes to broth and boil until done.
Remove bone and skin from chicken, pulling chicken into small pieces.
Add chicken and peas back to broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: stuffed veal cutlets
directions: Pound meat until 1/4-inch thick.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Brown sausage and drain thoroughly.
Stir sausage and celery into stuffing.
Press 1/2 cup stuffing on each piece of meat to 1/2-inch of edge.
Roll up, beginning at narrow ends and secure with wooden picks.
Brown veal in shortening.
Remove meat from pan; drain pan of fat and add soup and milk.
Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Add meat; cover and simmer 45 minutes, or until tender.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Dissolve jello by package instructions.
Add marshmallows and cook until melted.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients.
Congeal in mold of your choice.

title: "koulourakia" - easter cookies
directions: Melt butter.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar and eggs; beat for 10 minutes.
Add orange juice and whiskey and beat well. Add baking powder and beat well.
Add flour slowly.
Use mixer until it begins to thicken.
Knead in remaining flour until it makes a soft, non-sticky dough.
Pinch off pieces of dough and shape as desired.
Place on greased cookie sheets; brush with beaten egg yolk and sprinkle with sesame seed (optional).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: good stuff cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Punch holes in top of cake with handle of wooden spoon. Pour the Eagle Brand milk on top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with coconut.
Chill.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: With fork, poke hole in potatoes.
Place in microwave.
Bake on High 25 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut and serve with butter and salt.

title: layered turkey salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar; spread over turkey.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Cover and chill.

title: mock lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown meat and onion.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
In small bowl, cream together cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Drain meat.
Stir in tomato paste, sauce and seasonings.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, place 1/2 of noodles; top with 1/2 of meat mixture and 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Repeat with noodles, cheese mixture and then meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and melt.

title: baked rabbit(serves 4 to 5.  preparation time: 2 hours.)
directions: Put raw rice on the bottom of a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup with 2 cups water and pour half of soup over rice.
Place bite-size rabbit chunks on top of mixture.
Pour rest of soup on top of rabbit.
Cover tightly with tinfoil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Dust meat with flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Drain.
To the meat add broth and simmer until meat is tender.
Stir in soup.
Cook dumplings or noodles according to directioned on package and drain. Add to meat with Milnot.
Taste and add salt and pepper.
Cook until hot and well blended.

title: shoyu chicken (sugar-free)
directions: In a pot heat oil and stir-fry chicken until half cooked; drain oil and fat.
Mix in bowl, shoyu, water, ginger and Equal.
Cook chicken and onions for 5 minutes.
Pour shoyu mixture in with chicken.
Let simmer on low for 1 hour.
(Hint:
Cook on low heat so Equal sugar substitute doesn't lose its sweetness.)
Add extra water if too salty.
Season to taste.
Mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 1/3 cup cold water.
Add to simmering sauce to thicken.
Serve with hot rice.

title: meringue
directions: Beat 2 egg whites and a dash of salt until foamy.
Slowly add 1/4 cup sugar, beating constantly until stiff shiny peaks form. Pile onto pudding.
Seal edges.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes at 425° until lightly browned.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Good for dipping strawberries or any fruit.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Lay chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the next 3 ingredients well.
Pour the mixture over the chicken.
Let sauce and chicken sit for 1/2 hour to marinate.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Then uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer to brown the chicken.
Baste the chicken during the last 1/2 hour of baking.
Total baking time is 2 hours.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburg in large skillet and drain.
Boil macaroni in large pot and drain.
Mix hamburg, macaroni and tomatoes together. Pre-heat oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: ham balls (or loaf)
directions: Mix ham, pork, bread crumbs, milk and eggs.
Form into 1-inch balls or 3 loaves.
Pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting often.
Serve balls with toothpicks as appetizer or loaves for main course.

title: brian's grilled ginger salmon(servings:  4)
directions: Combine soy, ginger, brown sugar, olive oil, garlic, cayenne, basil and mirin in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring lightly. Pour sauce over salmon fillet and allow to marinate 30 minutes at room temperature.
After 30 minutes, pour marinade back into saucepan.
Cut salmon fillet into large steak (for ease of cooking).
Grill over very hot fire (cook skin side down first) for 2 to 3 minutes per side, no longer.
Bring marinade back to boil. Mix 1 tablespoon of cornstarch and 3 tablespoons of water.
Add cornstarch to marinade.
Cook at high heat until thickens.
Pour sauce over salmon and serve.
Suggested Wine:
Macon Villages - White Burgundy.
Serving Ideas:
Angel hair and pesto sauce is good.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour over apples and mix.
Pour in pie shell and top with second crust.
Great to freeze.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well; cover and simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for 4 pounds meat.

title: tuna corn chip salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn chips. Chill. Add chips just before serving. Serves about 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into thin slices.
Season with salt and pepper.
Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Brown meat, mushrooms and onion.
Mix flour and milk.
Add to meat.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add sour cream.
Serve over buttered noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated chicken
directions: One day before serving, place chicken in a shallow dish.
Pour lemon juice over chicken and marinate overnight, turning pieces occasionally.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove chicken from lemon juice; reserve juice.
Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge the chicken with seasoned flour and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake chicken for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: almond extract punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale and chill.
Add ginger ale when serving.
May use some of punch and add some fruit to make an ice ring.
Makes 1 gallon, plus 2 3/4 cups.
Serves 25.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread cooked, cooled refried beans on platter.
Spread mashed avocados on top of beans.
Sprinkle chopped green onions; spread mayonnaise.
Sprinkle diced tomatoes.
Spread and sprinkle grated cheese and finally sprinkle black olives on top for garnish. Serves a small party of 6.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Saute meat and onion until tender.
Drain well.
In a large skillet, add meat, onion, mushroom soup, beans and corn.
Stir together and add cooked egg noodles.
Pour into large casserole. Sprinkle dried onion rings on top.
Put in 350° oven.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: unbaked peanut butter cups
directions: Melt margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and frost over peanut butter mixture. When chocolate is set, cut into small squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place the rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour in water and stir.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice.
Pour or spoon can of mushroom soup over.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix over top and drizzle with sherry.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: bacon, onion, potato casserole
directions: Layer
potatoes, onion, apple and
bacon
in
casserole dish. Sprinkle each layer with very
little
sage and seasoning.	 Top layer should be potatoes.
Pour
water
over
top. Cover and cook at 325° for 2 hours.
Dot potatoes with butter, then bake until brown, 30 minutes.	Serves 6.

title: jack's italian cheesecake
directions: With electric mixer, cream cheeses together.
Add sugar and beat.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in lemon juice, cornstarch, flour and vanilla.
Add butter and mix until smooth.
Blend in sour cream.

title: crock-pot chicken soup
directions: Put cut up carrots and celery in bottom of crock-pot.
Add chicken, water and seasonings.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours (overnight).
Remove chicken and bones from broth.
Turn crock-pot to high and add 1 can cream of chicken soup and noodles.
Add deboned chicken.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Add 1 cup of milk at the last before serving.

title: shrimpola
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan.
Saute celery, bell pepper, onion, garlic, salt and pepper until tender.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook until tender. Serve over rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until crust is brown and custard is firm.

title: yogurt dinner rolls
directions: In saucepan, heat together yogurt, margarine, water and sugar until margarine is melted.
Set aside and let cool to lukewarm. In large bowl, combine yeast, 3/4 cup white flour, 3/4 cup whole wheat flour and baking soda.
Add cooled liquid mixture to yeast-flour mixture; then add eggs, spices and grated onion.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in 1/2 cup white flour and 3/4 cup whole wheat flour.
Dough will still be moist and a
little sticky. Place in a bowl sprayed with vegetable cooking spray, turning once.
Cover with a towel or plastic wrap.
Let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Place on floured board and knead lightly. Divide into 12 even pieces; form into round balls and place into muffin tins sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Cover; let rise about 40 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until nicely browned.
Remove from muffin tins immediately.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Yield:
1 dozen.
Approximate calories/serving:
1 roll = 140.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in 5-quart pot.
Drain off grease.
Add onion, beans, carrots, corn and cabbage.
Cook until carrots are tender, then add tomatoes and peas.
Cook on medium-high for 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Stir
together all ingredients except mandarin oranges. Add 2/3 of
oranges
last
and stir gently .
Arrange leftover oranges on top.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cold water buns
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ambrosia (dessert)
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix all the ingredients (except bananas) together. Let them stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Just before serving, add bananas.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gert's strawberry salad
directions: Bring 1 cup of water to a boil, mix in gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients (except sour cream) and stir.
Pour half of mixture in pan and let congeal.
Put sour cream over this and let set up about 2 hours.
Then spoon the rest of the gelatin mixture and let congeal.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in container of electric blender; process 30 seconds.
Let stand
5 minutes.
Combine flours in large bowl.
Add 1 cup flour mixture, sugar and remaining ingredients to yeast mixture in blender container; process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Gradually stir yeast mixture into remaining flour mixture to make a soft dough.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Add flour to sugar.
Mix all ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick, then flavor with lemon.
Pour into cooked crust.
Put egg whites on top and put in oven to brown.
This makes one large pie.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix sugar, lemon juice, flour, cinnamon, cream of tartar, salt and spice in a bowl. Fold in squash until coated.
Dot with butter.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell. Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream; set aside.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to package directions.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with a vegetable spray.
Pour the soup mixture over top of chicken.
Cover this with the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tallahassee rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger potato stuff
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add cubed potatoes (peeled), diced onion and tomato sauce.
Mix carefully with spatula.
Season with seasonings to taste.
Cover and simmer on low until potatoes are soft, stirring and mixing carefully every 10 minutes.
Serve with refried beans and flour tortillas. Build burritos or pinch tortillas and use as a scoop.

title: szechwan chicken pasta
directions: Cook linguine; keep warm.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Stir-fry garlic and ginger for 30 seconds.
Add chicken; fry 1 minute.
Add pea pods; fry 1 minute more.
Remove mixture from wok.
Add 1 tablespoon oil.
Stir-fry red and green peppers and onions for 2 minutes.
Return all to wok.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Place roast in dutch oven or large pot. Pour in beef broth.
Add the tomato paste and stir,
add the tomatoes,
blend in garlic, basil oregano, bay leaves. Cover and cook in oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn over meat and add the carrots, onions and mushrooms.
Cover and continue to cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mom's cooked chicken leftover
directions: Melt fat in milk, then cool.
Pour over beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and season.
Pour into greased casserole. Place in moderate oven at 350° until firm.
Serve with mushroom sauce.
Serves 6.

title: swiss cheese bread
directions: Bring milk and butter to a boil. Add salt and pepper. Add sifter flour all at one time. The dough will form a ball. Remove from heat. Add eggs one at a time and beat each egg until completely blended. Add approximately 3/4 of the Swiss cheese. Using about 2/3 of the dough, drop seven equal dollops on top a well greased cookie sheet in a circle, barely touching. Top each with a smaller dollop using the balance of the dough. Sprinkle the remaining cheese over the top. Bake approximately 55 minutes at 375°, or until rich golden brown. Separate and serve hot. Makes 7 servings.

title: hot apple punch
directions: Combine sugar, water and spices.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, 1 hour.
Strain.
Just before serving, combine syrup, fruit juices and cider.
Bring to boil quickly. Remove from heat; serve at once.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Cut the bacon into squares.
Fry.
Remove and dry on paper towel.
Pour 1/4 or 1/2 the fat over the diced potatoes.
Brown onion.
Add vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
When hot, add potatoes and bacon.
Heat thoroughly.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: gigi's apricot nut bread
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.
